INSERT INTO `administration_members` VALUES (11,'Dr','Dkt.','Ernest Francis Mabonesho',1,'Mkuu wa Chuo na Mtendaji Mkuu','Rector and Chief Executive Officer','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Dr. Ernest Francis Mabonesho is a Senior Lecturer and acting Rector and Chief Executive Officer at the Tanzania Public Service College (TPSC).&nbsp;&nbsp;He is a highly accomplished professional in the fields of accounts, finance, and education. He holds a PhD in Accounting and Finance and an MSc. International Accounting and Finance from the University of Strathclyde, United Kingdom (UK). He also holds a Bachelor of Arts in Education from the University of Dar es Salaam and a Diploma in Education from the Dar es Salaam Teachers College</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">In his current role as the acting Rector and Chief Executive Officer at TPSC, Dr. Mabonesho is responsible for overseeing the implementation of policies and initiatives aimed at enhancing the efficiency, transparency, and accountability of the public service sector. He is dedicated to promoting professional development, fostering a culture of integrity, and optimizing resource management within the public service.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">He joined Tanzania Public Service College in September 2021 as Deputy Rector of Planning, Finance, and Administration and assumed the role of Acting Rector and Chief Executive Officer in February 2023.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Before joining TPSC, Dr. Ernest was the Dean of the Faculty of Accounting, Banking, and Finance at the Institute of Financial Management (IFM). In this role, he exhibited exceptional leadership skills and a deep commitment to academic excellence in shaping the institute&#39;s curriculum, ensuring that students receive a comprehensive education in financial management and accounting.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Dr. Ernest Francis Mabonesho&#39;s remarkable academic background, combined with his experience and leadership skills, has made significant contributions to the development and advancement of the Tanzania Public College.</p>','<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Dr. Ernest Francis Mabonesho is a Senior Lecturer and acting Rector and Chief Executive Officer at the Tanzania Public Service College (TPSC).&nbsp;&nbsp;He is a highly accomplished professional in the fields of accounts, finance, and education. He holds a PhD in Accounting and Finance and an MSc. International Accounting and Finance from the University of Strathclyde, United Kingdom (UK). He also holds a Bachelor of Arts in Education from the University of Dar es Salaam and a Diploma in Education from the Dar es Salaam Teachers College</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">In his current role as the acting Rector and Chief Executive Officer at TPSC, Dr. Mabonesho is responsible for overseeing the implementation of policies and initiatives aimed at enhancing the efficiency, transparency, and accountability of the public service sector. He is dedicated to promoting professional development, fostering a culture of integrity, and optimizing resource management within the public service.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">He joined Tanzania Public Service College in September 2021 as Deputy Rector of Planning, Finance, and Administration and assumed the role of Acting Rector and Chief Executive Officer in February 2023.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Before joining TPSC, Dr. Ernest was the Dean of the Faculty of Accounting, Banking, and Finance at the Institute of Financial Management (IFM). In this role, he exhibited exceptional leadership skills and a deep commitment to academic excellence in shaping the institute&#39;s curriculum, ensuring that students receive a comprehensive education in financial management and accounting.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Dr. Ernest Francis Mabonesho&#39;s remarkable academic background, combined with his experience and leadership skills, has made significant contributions to the development and advancement of the Tanzania Public College.</p>','965a4bcdd92b970e2197be0ebb97381a.jpeg','info@tpsc.go.tz','+255 22 2152982','2023-12-14 07:32:11','2024-01-09 05:31:35','rector-and-chief-executive-officer'),(12,'Mr','Bw.','Shakiru Abdulkarim',0,'Mkuu wa Kitengo cha Mawasiliano na Masoko','Head of Communication and Marketing','<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Shakiru Abdulkarim ni mtaalamu mwenye uzoefu wa miaka kumi na tisa katika nyanja za mawasiliano ya umma, masoko na usimamizi wa mradi. Kwa sasa anahudumu kama Mkuu wa Kitengo Mawasiliano na Masoko anayehusika na kupanga, kuendeleza na kutekeleza mikakati ya mawasiliano na masoko na kusimamia shughuli za mahusiano ya umma ya Chuo.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Kabla ya kujiunga na Chuo, Shakiru amewahi kufanya kazi na Wakala wa Mafunzo kwa Njia ya Mtandao (TaGLA) kama Afisa Mkuu wa Masoko, Taasisi ya Miradi na Maendeleo ya Miundombinu ya UTT ( UTT-PID) kama Msimamizi Mkuu wa Miradi, na Dhamana ya Uwekezaji Tanzania ( UTT) &nbsp;kama Afisa Mwendaji Mkuu na Kampuni ya Mawasiliano Tanzania (TTCL )kama Afisa Huduma kwa Wateja.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Akiwa na uzoefu mkubwa katika mawasiliano ya umma, Masoko, usimamizi wa miradi, na uendeshaji, Shakiru anaendelea kutoa mchango muhimu katika kuleta mafanikio kwa chou.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Shakiru ana Shahada ya Kwanza ya Sanaa na Shahada ya Uzamili ya Usimamizi &nbsp;wa Biashara katika Masoko kutoka Chuo Kikuu cha Dar es Salaam na Chuo Kikuu Huria cha Tanzania mtawalia.</p>','<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Shakiru Abdulkarim is a dynamic professional with nineteen years of extensive experience in the fields of corporate communication, marketing, and project management. Currently serving as the Head of Communication and Marketing responsible for planning, development, and implementation of college marketing strategies, communications, and public relations activities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Shakiru has previously worked with Tanzania Global Learning Agency as Principal Marketing Officer, UTT Projects and Infrastructure Development PLC as Head of Project Management, Unit Trust of Tanzania as Principal Operations Offer, and Tanzania Telecommunication Company Ltd as Customer Service officer.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">With his strong background in communication, marketing, project management, and operations, Shakiru continues to make valuable contributions in driving success for the college and achieving remarkable results.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">He holds a Bachelor of Arts with horns and a Master of Business Administration in Marketing from the University of Dar es Salaam and Open University of Tanzania respectively.</p>','94e56ab29dd3a01be6ba6a0b4c7ffbdb.jpeg','abdulkarim.shakiru@tpsc.go.tz','+2556542428','2023-12-14 08:31:59','2024-01-02 11:23:15','head-of-communication-and-marketinging'),(13,'Mr.','Bw.','Mussa Lugembe',0,'Mkurugenzi wa Kampasi - Dar es Salaam','Campus Director - Dar es Salaam',NULL,NULL,'3b6f99aa2d4bb3dce669e5456fe40178.jpeg','mussa.lugembe@tpsc.go.tz','+255 22 2152982','2023-12-14 08:36:44','2023-12-19 08:20:29','campus-director-dar-es-salaam'),(14,'Mr','Mr','Jovinus Christopher',0,'Ag.HPMU','Ag.HPMU','<p>Acting Head of Procurement Manangement Unit</p>','<p>Acting Head of Procurement Manangement Unit</p>','2826e6b3ddc2bc53824cb16b768c0344.jpeg','info@tpsc.go.tz','+255 22 2152982','2023-12-14 08:49:36','2023-12-19 08:14:08','ag-hpmu'),(15,'Mr.','Ndg.','Elibarick Mushi',0,'Kaimu Mkurugenzi - Huduma Wezeshi za Taaluma','Ag. Director - Academic Supports Services','<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Bw. Elibarick Mushi aliteuliwa kushika nafasi ya Mkurugenzi wa huduma wezeshi za Taaluma (Kaimu) tangu mwezi Novemba 2023. Kabla ya nafasi hiyo, amepata fursa ya kutumikia katika nafasi mbalimbali katika Chuo cha Utumishi wa Umma Tanzania kama vile Kusimamia Kitengo cha Udhibiti/Uhakiki Ubora (Mwaka mmoja na nusu), Kusimamia Kitengo cha TEHAMA (Mwaka mmoja na nusu), Meneja Mafunzo (Miaka Minne), Mkuu wa Kitengo cha Usajili na Mitihani katika Kampasi (Miaka mitatu), na Mratibu wa TeHAMA katika Kampasi (Mwaka Mmoja). Kabla ya kujiunga na Chuo cha Utumishi wa Umma Tanzania, ametumika kama Mhadhiri Msaidizi, na Mhadhiri Mwandamizi katika chuo cha Kimataifa cha Kampala kwa kipindi cha miaka minne.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Akiwa na Uzoefu wa Miaka 13 kwenye tasnia ya mafunzo katika vyuo, ikiambatana na dhamira ya dhati ya kutumia TEHAMA kuboresha utendaji kazi za taasisi, Elibarick amekuwa na mchango mkubwa katika kuibua vipaji vya kizazi kipya cha wataalamu wa TEHAMA pamoja na kuwahamasisha wanachuo wa fani nyingine kutumia vema TEHAMA katika kuongeza tija kwenye majukumu yao kazini. Maeneo yake ya Ubobevu kitaaluma ni Lugha za Computer, Mifumo Mtandao, Utengenezaji Mifumo, Uundaji wa Kanzidata, na Programu rahisishi za kazi za Ofisi.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Mbali na kushiri katika kazi za taaluma,&nbsp; fursa aliyopata ya kutumika katika nafasi mbalimbali za uongozi na utawala zimempa uzoefu katika maeneo ya Utawala, Uundaji na Usimamizi wa Utekelezaji wa Mitaala ya vyuo, Uundaji wa Sera, Udhibiti/Uhakiki ubora wa Vyuo na Uratibu wa Kazi za kamati za taaluma vyuoni.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Kielimu, Elibarick ana Shahada ya Kwanza ya Menejimenti ya Mifumo na Shahada ya Uzamili ya Mifumo.</p>','<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Mr. Elibarick Mushi assumed the role of Director of Academic Support Services (Acting) in November 2023. Prior to his current position, he served in various key roles at Tanzania Public Service College, including Head of Quality Assurance (1.5 years), Head of ICT (1.5 years), Manager of Programmes (4 years), Campus Head of Admission and Examination Unit (3 years), and Campus ICT Coordinator (1 year). Before joining TPSC, he served for four years as an Assistant Lecturer and Tutorial Assistant at Kampala International University.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">With 13 years of dedicated experience in higher education, coupled with passion about utilizing technology to enhance business operations, Elibarick has played a pivotal role in shaping the next generation of ICT professionals and inspiring students from diverse fields to leverage ICT for improved performance in their respective professions. His training expertise spans computer programming, web applications development, Information Systems, database design, and office applications.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">In addition to his teaching roles, Elibarick&#39;s exposure to managerial and administrative duties has honed his skills in Administration, Curriculum Development and Implementation, Policy Formulation, Quality Assurance in Colleges, and Academic Committees&rsquo; Management.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Elibarick holds a Bachelor&#39;s degree in Management Information Systems and a Master&#39;s degree in Information Systems.</p>','b1231bf5b1de054f090b00c11b204416.jpeg','elibarick.mushi@tpsc.go.tz','0753860432','2023-12-14 08:49:50','2023-12-19 08:07:01','director'),(16,'Mr.','Ndg.','Sijali Korojelo',0,'Mkurugenzi','Director','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Sijali Petro Korojelo ni Kaimu Mkurugenzi wa Mafunzo kwa Watumishi wa Umma wa Chuo cha Utumishi wa Umma Tanzania tangu Februari 2023. Kabla ya hapo, amewahi kufanya kazi kama Meneja Mafunzo wa Kampasi ya Mtwara (2016), Mkurugenzi wa Kampasi za Tanga na Singida (2017-2019) na Kaimu Mkurugenzi wa Kituo cha Mafunzo kwa Njia ya Mtandao cha Chuo cha Utumishi wa Umma Tanzania (2020-2022). Korojelo pia amewahi kuhudumu kama mtafiti katika idara ya Tehama ya Chuo Kikuu cha Amsterdam, Uholanzi (2011-2012).</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Korojelo ana shahada ya kwanza na shahada ya uzamili katika Sayansi ya Kompyuta toka Chuo Kikuu cha Dar es Salaam. Amewahi pia kuhudhuria mafunzo kadhaa ya kujenga umahiri katika maeneo ya uongozi, utawala na TEHAMA. Maeneo yake pendwa ya tafiti ni pamoja na uongozi, utawala, mifumo ya Tehama, kanzudata za TEHAMA pamoja na mitandao ya kompyuta.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Katika vipindi vyake mbalimbali vya kuhudumu, Korojelo ametoa machapisho kadhaa katika maeneo ya TEHAMA na menejimenti.</p>','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Sijali Petro Korojelo has been the acting Director of Public Service in Service Training since February 2023. In the past, he served as the manager of programme at the TPSC Mtwara campus (2016), a campus director for the Singida and Tanga campuses (2017 - 2019), and an acting director of the Global Learning Centre (2020 - 2022). Furthermore, he once served as a researcher at the Informatics Institute of the University of Amsterdam, Netherlands (2011 - 2012).</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Korojelo holds a bachelor&#39;s and a master&rsquo;s degree in Computer Science from the University of Dar es Salaam. He has also attended several professional training programme in the areas of computing and ICT. His areas of interest include management, administration, information systems, databases, computer networking, and cloud computing.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">During the course of his actions, Korojelo has published several articles in the areas of management, computing, and ICT. Some of his publications include Enhanced Authentication on Targeted Online Surveys: A Case of Online Course Evaluation System (at the International Journal on New Computer Architectures and Their Applications), Online&nbsp;Surveys System with Enhanced Authentication Intelligence: A Case of Online Course Evaluation System (at Springer), and Uplifting Motivation of Tanzanian Public Service Personnel for Improved Service Delivery: The Reflection of Public Service Motivation Theory (at the International Journal of African and Asian.</p>','4cb1079629c181bd699f9ba18e9a057a.jpeg','sijali.korojelo@tpsc.go.tz','+255 22 2152982','2023-12-14 08:52:23','2024-01-09 05:34:52','director-2'),(17,'Ms','Ms','Juslina Tuzza',0,'Mkurugenzi wa Kampasi ya Mtwara','Campus Director -  Mtwara','<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Ms. Juslina M.Tuzza is An Assistant Lecturer and Campus Director at the Tanzania Public Service College (TPSC) - Mtwara Campus. &nbsp;She is a highly accomplished professional in the fields of education (Language). She holds a Master&rsquo;s Degree of Arts with Education from the University of Dar es Salaam, Tanzania. She also holds a Bachelor of Arts with Education from the University of St. John Dodoma-Tanzania and a Diploma in Education from the Marangu Teachers&rsquo; College- Kilimanjaro, Tanzania.<br />\r\nIn March 2021, she joined Tanzania Public Service Collage as Assistant lecturer, where latter promoted to the position of Manager of Program at Campus level, a position she held until February 2022, when she was appointed as Campus Director at Mtwara campus working from February 2022 to date</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><br />\r\nIn her role as the Campus Director at Tanzania Public Service College- Mtwara, Ms. Tuzza is responsible for the implementation of all policies and initiatives aimed at ensuring the efficiency and accountability of the campus staff and students in implementing their responsibilities to make sure specific and general goals of the organization are well attained. She is highly dedicated and her successful career path and an upward mobility that is matched and can only be explained by factors of individual motivation and personal discipline as well as sense of self-awareness fueled by her individual strong and persistence philosophy of life.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><br />\r\nMs. Juslina M Tuzza has a remarkable academic background, combined with her experiences and skills have made significant contributions to the development and advancement of the Tanzania Public College at Mtwara Campus and Nation at large. Besides, She has successfully prepared papers for publication; The Perception of Job seekers on the Adoption and Use of E-Recruitment in Tanzania:A case study of Ajira Portal, Challenges of &nbsp;&lsquo; Gheto&rsquo; life to Students in Vocational &nbsp;Education and Training Institutions; The case of Mtwara &nbsp;region and &nbsp;Exploring &nbsp;the Influence of Parenting &nbsp;Style on Adolescents&rsquo; Sexual Behavior (Prostitution) in Chris Mwangi&rsquo;s The Operator. Further underscoring her unwavering commitment to advancing the fields of education and personal development. She frequently involved in personal academic studies online and attending short course training particularly on data collection and analysis.</p>','<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Ms. Juslina M.Tuzza is An Assistant Lecturer and Campus Director at the Tanzania Public Service College (TPSC) - Mtwara Campus. &nbsp;She is a highly accomplished professional in the fields of education (Language). She holds a Master&rsquo;s Degree of Arts with Education from the University of Dar es Salaam, Tanzania. She also holds a Bachelor of Arts with Education from the University of St. John Dodoma-Tanzania and a Diploma in Education from the Marangu Teachers&rsquo; College- Kilimanjaro, Tanzania.<br />\r\nIn March 2021, she joined Tanzania Public Service Collage as Assistant lecturer, where latter promoted to the position of Manager of Program at Campus level, a position she held until February 2022, when she was appointed as Campus Director at Mtwara campus working from February 2022 to date</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><br />\r\nIn her role as the Campus Director at Tanzania Public Service College- Mtwara, Ms. Tuzza is responsible for the implementation of all policies and initiatives aimed at ensuring the efficiency and accountability of the campus staff and students in implementing their responsibilities to make sure specific and general goals of the organization are well attained. She is highly dedicated and her successful career path and an upward mobility that is matched and can only be explained by factors of individual motivation and personal discipline as well as sense of self-awareness fueled by her individual strong and persistence philosophy of life.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><br />\r\nMs. Juslina M Tuzza has a remarkable academic background, combined with her experiences and skills have made significant contributions to the development and advancement of the Tanzania Public College at Mtwara Campus and Nation at large. Besides, She has successfully prepared papers for publication; The Perception of Job seekers on the Adoption and Use of E-Recruitment in Tanzania:A case study of Ajira Portal, Challenges of &nbsp;&lsquo; Gheto&rsquo; life to Students in Vocational &nbsp;Education and Training Institutions; The case of Mtwara &nbsp;region and &nbsp;Exploring &nbsp;the Influence of Parenting &nbsp;Style on Adolescents&rsquo; Sexual Behavior (Prostitution) in Chris Mwangi&rsquo;s The Operator. Further underscoring her unwavering commitment to advancing the fields of education and personal development. She frequently involved in personal academic studies online and attending short course training particularly on data collection and analysis.</p>','c169c419cbfa83870ad64df47a602160.jpeg','juslina.tuzza@tpsc.go.tz','Phone: +255 232 333300','2023-12-14 08:55:16','2024-01-11 03:55:25','campus-manager-mtwara-campus'),(18,NULL,NULL,'Edith Rwiza',0,'Mjumbe wa Bodi','Board Member','<p>&nbsp;Dkt. Edith Rwiza ni mjumber wa Bodi ya Ushauri ya Chuo cha Utumishi wa Umma...........</p>','<p>Dr. Edith Rwiza is a member of TPSC Ministerial Advisory Board.................</p>','7d85839e73261353ea555b1f8f824967.png','info@tpsc.go.tz','+255222152982','2023-12-14 09:04:48','2023-12-14 09:08:13','board-member'),(19,'Dr','Dkt','Hamisi Amani',0,'Kaimu Makamu Mkuu wa Chuo Taaluma','Ag. Deputy Rector-Academic, Research and Consultancy','<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\">Dr. Hamisi Amani is a renowned scholar and visionary leader in the field of education, linguistics and public service currently serving as Ag. Deputy Rector, Academic, research and Consultancy at Tanzania Public Service College (TPSC).</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\">Dr. Amani&#39;s passion for education led him to pursue a degree which led to an award of Bachelor of Arts with Education at the University of Dar es salaam, where he graduated with honor degree in 2007. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\">Following his Bachelor&#39;s, Dr. Amani obtained a Master&#39;s degree in linguistics from the University of Dar es Salaam in 2010. During his time at the University of Dar es salaam, he immersed himself in various research projects, focusing particularly on contact linguistics and participated in part time basis in the Language of Tanzania Project (LOT) in the development of the Makonde Dictionary. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\">Driven by a desire to make a tangible contribution in education, Dr. Amani went on to pursue a Ph.D. in Linguistics at the University of Dar es Salaam. His doctoral research focused on analyzing the interplay of social and linguistic factors in structural borrowing from Kiswahili into Chimalaba. His findings highlighted the need for comprehensive strategies that address issues of the influence of Kiswahili on Ethnic Community Languages (ECLs) in Tanzania focusing on the impact of language change. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\">Upon completing his doctorate, Dr. Amani got a chance to serve in different leadership positions at Tanzania Public Service College (TPSC). He served as the Head of Research, Consultancy and Short Course Department and Head of Public Administration, Leadership and Management Department both at Mtwara Campus. He was then appointed to serve as Campus Director at Singida campus from 2019 to 2023 when he was appointed to the current position of Acting Deputy Rector, Academic, research and Consultancy. In all those leadership roles, Dr. Amani positioned himself as a thought leader in the public service through Tanzania Public Service College and contributed in advising the government and its institutions through his scholarly works of consultancy, research and publications. &nbsp;</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\">In addition to his leadership roles, Dr. Amani has deeply engaged in scholarly works. In consultancy, he has recently engaged in national consultancy works of reviewing and preparation of National Multi-sectoral HIV and AIDS Stigma and Discrimination Reduction Strategy of the Year 2013-2017 for TACAIDS in 2022 and Conducting Stigma Index 2.0 Survey for PLHIV in Tanzania Mainland from 2020 to 2021 for TACAIDS. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\">In research, Dr. Amani has conducted research on various issues in the public service such as Learning Transfer, Challenges in the Implementation of OPRAS in LGAs, Poverty and Vulnerability Surveys and implementation of staff induction training.&nbsp; He has published extensively in his field of linguistics and in the public service. </span></span></span></span></p>','<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\">Dr. Hamisi Amani is a renowned scholar and visionary leader in the field of education, linguistics and public service currently serving as Ag. Deputy Rector, Academic, research and Consultancy at Tanzania Public Service College (TPSC).</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\">Dr. Amani&#39;s passion for education led him to pursue a degree which led to an award of Bachelor of Arts with Education at the University of Dar es salaam, where he graduated with honor degree in 2007. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\">Following his Bachelor&#39;s, Dr. Amani obtained a Master&#39;s degree in linguistics from the University of Dar es Salaam in 2010. During his time at the University of Dar es salaam, he immersed himself in various research projects, focusing particularly on contact linguistics and participated in part time basis in the Language of Tanzania Project (LOT) in the development of the Makonde Dictionary. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\">Driven by a desire to make a tangible contribution in education, Dr. Amani went on to pursue a Ph.D. in Linguistics at the University of Dar es Salaam. His doctoral research focused on analyzing the interplay of social and linguistic factors in structural borrowing from Kiswahili into Chimalaba. His findings highlighted the need for comprehensive strategies that address issues of the influence of Kiswahili on Ethnic Community Languages (ECLs) in Tanzania focusing on the impact of language change. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\">Upon completing his doctorate, Dr. Amani got a chance to serve in different leadership positions at Tanzania Public Service College (TPSC). He served as the Head of Research, Consultancy and Short Course Department and Head of Public Administration, Leadership and Management Department both at Mtwara Campus. He was then appointed to serve as Campus Director at Singida campus from 2019 to 2023 when he was appointed to the current position of Acting Deputy Rector, Academic, research and Consultancy. In all those leadership roles, Dr. Amani positioned himself as a thought leader in the public service through Tanzania Public Service College and contributed in advising the government and its institutions through his scholarly works of consultancy, research and publications. &nbsp;</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\">In addition to his leadership roles, Dr. Amani has deeply engaged in scholarly works. In consultancy, he has recently engaged in national consultancy works of reviewing and preparation of National Multi-sectoral HIV and AIDS Stigma and Discrimination Reduction Strategy of the Year 2013-2017 for TACAIDS in 2022 and Conducting Stigma Index 2.0 Survey for PLHIV in Tanzania Mainland from 2020 to 2021 for TACAIDS. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\">In research, Dr. Amani has conducted research on various issues in the public service such as Learning Transfer, Challenges in the Implementation of OPRAS in LGAs, Poverty and Vulnerability Surveys and implementation of staff induction training.&nbsp; He has published extensively in his field of linguistics and in the public service. </span></span></span></span></p>','e632e3684ff354e9d0ad1fc95c6a4fd9.jpeg','info@tpsc.go.tz','+255 22 2152982','2023-12-14 09:07:07','2024-01-02 05:26:50','ag-deputy-rector-academic-research-and-consultancy'),(21,'Mr','Mr','Hermes A. Assenga',0,'Ag.HICT','Ag.HICT','<p>Ag.HICT</p>','<p>Ag.HICT</p>','511dfa7041c02f7c4e70fb2f93b2658d.jpeg','info@tpsc.go.tz','+255 22 2152982','2023-12-14 09:09:37','2023-12-19 05:56:58','ag-hict'),(22,'Ms.','Bi.','Zawadi Rashid',0,'Mkurugenzi','Director','<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit, sed do eiusmod tempor incididunt ut labore et dolore magna aliqua. Ut enim ad minim veniam, quis nostrud exercitation ullamco laboris nisi ut aliquip ex ea commodo consequat. Duis aute irure 