INSERT INTO `campuses` VALUES (4,'<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The Tanzania Public Service College Dar es salaam Campus (TPSC) is among of the six campuses for Tanzania Public service College, The campus performs all three core functions of the College which includes Training, Consultancy and Applied Research, but also the Campus provide review Programs for Public Service Examinations, and other Performance Improvement Programs with the aim of building a culture of continuous learning for public servants.</p>','<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Current the Campus runs a range of Programmes from NTA Level 4 to NTA Level 8 which is offered by different Academic Departments such as: Public Sector Financial Management (PSFM), Secretarial Studies (SS), Records and Archives Management (RAM), Public Administration, Leadership and Management (PALM).</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Since the establishment of the Campus, the Campus had been offering Programs at Certificate and Diploma levels, yet in meeting Customer needs, the Campus started offering a Bachelor Degree in the areas of Secretarial Studies and records, archives and Information management since September 2017 with a total number of 200 students of which some of them who where qualified for the Loans they are the beneficiary of Loans from the Higher Education Loan Board.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Currently the Campus is expecting to run only two Programs; Records management and Secretarial Studies from NTA level 4 to NTA lever 8. At the moment Campus has more than 35 qualified Teaching Staff</p>','<p>Student Services Helpdesk</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Gender and Help Desk</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Accommodation Offices&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Useful Contact Details</p>','<p>Classrooms and Hall</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Typing Laboratories</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Computer Laboratories&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Library</p>','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Mkurugenzi wa Kampasi</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Chuo Cha Utumishi wa Umma Tanzania&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>S.L.P&nbsp; 2574</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Dar es Salaam</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Simu: +255 22 2123547/9, 2122243</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Barua pepe:&nbsp; dsm@tpsc.go.tz</p>','<p>The Tanzania Public Service College Dar es salaam Campus (TPSC) is among of the six campuses for Tanzania Public service College, The campus performs all three core functions of the College which includes Training, Consultancy and Applied Research, but also the Campus provide review Programs for Public Service Examinations, and other Performance Improvement Programs with the aim of building a culture of continuous learning for public servants.</p>','<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Current the Campus runs a range of Programmes from NTA Level 4 to NTA Level 8 which is offered by different Academic Departments such as: Public Sector Financial Management (PSFM), Secretarial Studies (SS), Records and Archives Management (RAM), Public Administration, Leadership and Management (PALM).</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Since the establishment of the Campus, the Campus had been offering Programs at Certificate and Diploma levels, yet in meeting Customer needs, the Campus started offering a Bachelor Degree in the areas of Secretarial Studies and records, archives and Information management since September 2017 with a total number of 200 students of which some of them who where qualified for the Loans they are the beneficiary of Loans from the Higher Education Loan Board.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Currently the Campus is expecting to run only two Programs; Records management and Secretarial Studies from NTA level 4 to NTA lever 8. At the moment Campus has more than 35 qualified Teaching Staff</p>','<p>Student Services Helpdesk</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Gender and Help Desk</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Accommodation Offices&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Useful Contact Details</p>','<p>Classrooms and Hall</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Typing Laboratories</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Computer Laboratories&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Library</p>','<p>&nbsp;Dar es salaam Campus is located at Magogoni Street Opposite Prime Minister Office along Kivukoni Road</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Campus Director</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Tanzania Public Service College</p>\r\n\r\n<p>P.O Box 2574</p>\r\n\r\n<p>DSM</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Tel: +255 22 2123547/9, 2122243</p>\r\n\r\n<p>E mail dsm@tpsc.go.tz</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','dar-es-salaam-campus','Kampasi ya Dar es Salaam','Dar es Salaam Campus','2024-01-11 07:19:27','2024-01-11 04:19:27'),(5,'<p>Who are we?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Tanzania Public Service College (TPSC) Tanga campus was established in July 2014, being the fourth campus to be established among the six campuses of TPSC. It&rsquo;s establishment was a result of instructions issued by prime minister Hon. Mizengo Pinda on 23th November 2009 during inauguration of Tanzania Public Service College Mtwara Campus.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>At the time of its establishment, it had only one academic programme (i.e. Basic Technician Certificate in Records Management), with 453 students and 9 instructors. At the moment the college has over 5 courses, with more than 50 instructors and over 1,600 students.</p>','<ol>\r\n	<li>Records, Archives and Information Management</li>\r\n	<li>Secretarial Studies</li>\r\n	<li>Human Resource Management</li>\r\n	<li>Public Administration</li>\r\n	<li>Procurement and Supply Management</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','<ol>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,\"><span style=\"color:#1d1d1b\">Career counselling&nbsp;</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,\"><span style=\"color:#1d1d1b\">Healthcare</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,\"><span style=\"color:#1d1d1b\">Networking training and events</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,\"><span style=\"color:#1d1d1b\">Student counsellor</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,\"><span style=\"color:#1d1d1b\">Student sports</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,\"><span style=\"color:#1d1d1b\">Students Organizations</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ol>','<ol>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,\"><strong><span style=\"color:#1d1d1b\">Study training and workshops</span></strong></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,\"><strong><span style=\"color:#1d1d1b\">Typing and Computer labs</span></strong></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,\"><strong><span style=\"color:#1d1d1b\">Hostel</span></strong></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,\"><strong><span style=\"color:#1d1d1b\">Canteen</span></strong></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,\"><strong><span style=\"color:#1d1d1b\">Stationaries</span></strong></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ol>','<p><em>Campus Director ,</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Tanzania Public Service College</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>P.O. Box 750</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Tanga</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a name=\"_GoBack\"></a><em>Tel:</em><em>&nbsp;</em><em>+</em><em>255-272977124</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Fax:</em><em>&nbsp;<em>+255-<em>272977125</em></em></em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Email::</em><em>&nbsp;tanga@tpsc.go.tz</em></p>','<p>Who are we?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Tanzania Public Service College (TPSC) Tanga campus was established in July 2014, being the fourth campus to be established among the six campuses of TPSC. It&rsquo;s establishment was a result of instructions issued by prime minister Hon. Mizengo Pinda on 23th November 2009 during inauguration of Tanzania Public Service College Mtwara Campus.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>At the time of its establishment, it had only one academic programme (i.e. Basic Technician Certificate in Records Management), with 453 students and 9 instructors. At the moment the college has over 5 courses, with more than 50 instructors and over 1,600 students.</p>','<ol>\r\n	<li>Records, Archives and Information Management</li>\r\n	<li>Secretarial Studies</li>\r\n	<li>Human Resource Management</li>\r\n	<li>Public Administration</li>\r\n	<li>Procurement and Supply Management</li>\r\n</ol>','<ol>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,\"><span style=\"color:#1d1d1b\">Career counselling&nbsp;</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,\"><span style=\"color:#1d1d1b\">Healthcare</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,\"><span style=\"color:#1d1d1b\">Networking training and events</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,\"><span style=\"color:#1d1d1b\">Student counsellor</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,\"><span style=\"color:#1d1d1b\">Student sports</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,\"><span style=\"color:#1d1d1b\">Students Organizations</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ol>','<ol>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,\"><strong><span style=\"color:#1d1d1b\">Study training and workshops</span></strong></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,\"><strong><span style=\"color:#1d1d1b\">Typing and Computer labs</span></strong></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,\"><strong><span style=\"color:#1d1d1b\">Hostel</span></strong></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,\"><strong><span style=\"color:#1d1d1b\">Canteen</span></strong></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,\"><strong><span style=\"color:#1d1d1b\">Stationaries</span></strong></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ol>','<p><em>Campus Director ,</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Tanzania Public Service College</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>P.O. Box 750</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Tanga</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a name=\"_GoBack\"></a><em>Tel:</em><em>&nbsp;</em><em>+</em><em>255-272977124</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Fax:</em><em>&nbsp;<em>+255-<em>272977125</em></em></em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Email::</em><em>&nbsp;tanga@tpsc.go.tz</em></p>','tanga','Kampasi ya Tanga','Tanga Campus','2024-01-11 07:19:12','2024-01-11 04:19:12'),(6,'<p><strong><em>Who are We?</em></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Tanzania Public Service College (TPSC) Mbeya Campus was established in July 2014, being the sixth campus to be established among the six campuses of TPSC. Its establishment was a result of instructions issued by Prime Minister Hon. Mizengo Pinda on 23<sup>rd</sup>&nbsp;November 2009 during the inauguration of Tanzania Public Service College Mtwara Campus.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>At the time of its establishment, it had only one academic programme (i.e Basic Technician Certificate in Records Management) with 453 Students and 5 instructors</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><em>Where are we?</em></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>TPSC Mbeya Campus is located at Sokomatola area nearby CCM regional offices.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Google Map</strong></p>','<p>&nbsp;Courses Offered are as shown here under.</p>\r\n\r\n<table cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse; width:531px\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:none; border-left:none; border-right:none; border-top:none; height:19px; vertical-align:bottom; white-space:nowrap; width:531px\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li><span style=\"font-size:15px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">Ordinary Diploma in Human Resource Management (ODHRM)&ndash;NTA 5 &amp; 6</span></span></li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:none; border-left:none; border-right:none; border-top:none; height:19px; vertical-align:bottom; white-space:nowrap\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li><span style=\"font-size:15px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">Ordinary Diploma in Secretarial Studies (ODSS) &ndash; NTA 5 &amp; 6</span></span></li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:none; border-left:none; border-right:none; border-top:none; height:19px; vertical-align:bottom; white-space:nowrap\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li><span style=\"font-size:15px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">Ordinary Diploma in Records Management (ODRM) (NTA 5 &amp; 6)</span></span></li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:none; border-left:none; border-right:none; border-top:none; height:19px; vertical-align:bottom; white-space:nowrap\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li><span style=\"font-size:15px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">Ordinary Diploma in Local Government Administration (NTA5,6)</span></span></li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:none; border-left:none; border-right:none; border-top:none; height:19px; vertical-align:bottom; white-space:nowrap\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li><span style=\"font-size:15px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">Basic Technician Certificate in Records Management (BTCRM)&nbsp; NTA 4</span></span></li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:none; border-left:none; border-right:none; border-top:none; height:19px; vertical-align:bottom; white-space:nowrap\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li><span style=\"font-size:15px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">Basic Technician Certificate in Secretarial Studies (BTCSS) &ndash; NTA 4</span></span></li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:none; border-left:none; border-right:none; border-top:none; height:19px; vertical-align:bottom; white-space:nowrap\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li><span style=\"font-size:15px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">Basic Technician Certificate in Public Administration (BTCPA) &ndash; NTA 4</span></span></li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:none; border-left:none; border-right:none; border-top:none; height:19px; vertical-align:bottom; white-space:nowrap\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li><span style=\"font-size:15px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">Basic Technician Certificate in Human Resource Management (BTCHRM) &ndash; NTA 4</span></span></li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>','<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Academic Advising:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Assistance in course selection</li>\r\n		<li>Academic planning and progress tracking</li>\r\n		<li>Guidance on major and career choices</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Counseling Services:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Personal counseling</li>\r\n		<li>Career counseling</li>\r\n		<li>Mental health support</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Library Services:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Access to books, journals, and other resources</li>\r\n		<li>Research assistance and guidance</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Tutoring and Academic Support:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Peer tutoring services</li>\r\n		<li>Writing centers</li>\r\n		<li>Supplemental instruction programs</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Career Services:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Resume writing and interview preparation</li>\r\n		<li>Job search assistance</li>\r\n		<li>Career fairs and networking events</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Health Services:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Basic medical care</li>\r\n		<li>Counseling on health and wellness</li>\r\n		<li>Immunization and preventive health services</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>','<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Classrooms and Lecture Halls:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Equipped with audio-visual aids for effective teaching and learning.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Libraries:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Access to a collection of books, journals, and electronic resources.</li>\r\n		<li>Quiet study areas and collaborative spaces.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Laboratories:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Science labs for physics, chemistry, biology, etc.</li>\r\n		<li>Computer labs for programming, research, and general use.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Auditoriums and Theaters:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Spaces for large lectures, presentations, performances, and events.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Recreational Areas:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Sports fields, courts, and facilities for various sports.</li>\r\n		<li>Gyms and fitness centers.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Housing and Residential Facilities:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>On-campus dormitories or housing options.</li>\r\n		<li>Common areas and lounges for residents.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Dining Halls and Cafeterias:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Food services providing meals for students.</li>\r\n		<li>Options for different dietary preferences.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Student Centers:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Central hub for student activities and services.</li>\r\n		<li>Meeting rooms, event spaces, and student organization offices.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Health and Wellness Centers:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Medical clinics for basic healthcare.</li>\r\n		<li>Counseling services for mental health support.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>','<p><strong><u>Contacts</u></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Campus Director</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Tanzania Public Service College</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>P.O Box 1207</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Mbeya</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Phone<a name=\"_GoBack\"></a></em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Fax +255-252502627</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>E-mail: mbeya@tpsc.go.tz</em></p>','<p><strong><em>Who are We?</em></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Tanzania Public Service College (TPSC) Mbeya Campus was established in July 2014, being the sixth campus to be established among the six campuses of TPSC. Its establishment was a result of instructions issued by Prime Minister Hon. Mizengo Pinda on 23<sup>rd</sup>&nbsp;November 2009 during the inauguration of Tanzania Public Service College Mtwara Campus.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>At the time of its establishment, it had only one academic programme (i.e Basic Technician Certificate in Records Management) with 453 Students and 5 instructors</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><em>Where are we?</em></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>TPSC Mbeya Campus is located at Sokomatola area nearby CCM regional offices.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Google Map</strong></p>','<p>&nbsp;Courses Offered are as shown here under.</p>\r\n\r\n<table cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse; width:531px\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:none; border-left:none; border-right:none; border-top:none; height:19px; vertical-align:bottom; white-space:nowrap; width:531px\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li><span style=\"font-size:15px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">Ordinary Diploma in Human Resource Management (ODHRM)&ndash;NTA 5 &amp; 6</span></span></li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:none; border-left:none; border-right:none; border-top:none; height:19px; vertical-align:bottom; white-space:nowrap\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li><span style=\"font-size:15px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">Ordinary Diploma in Secretarial Studies (ODSS) &ndash; NTA 5 &amp; 6</span></span></li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:none; border-left:none; border-right:none; border-top:none; height:19px; vertical-align:bottom; white-space:nowrap\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li><span style=\"font-size:15px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">Ordinary Diploma in Records Management (ODRM) (NTA 5 &amp; 6)</span></span></li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:none; border-left:none; border-right:none; border-top:none; height:19px; vertical-align:bottom; white-space:nowrap\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li><span style=\"font-size:15px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">Ordinary Diploma in Local Government Administration (NTA5,6)</span></span></li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:none; border-left:none; border-right:none; border-top:none; height:19px; vertical-align:bottom; white-space:nowrap\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li><span style=\"font-size:15px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">Basic Technician Certificate in Records Management (BTCRM)&nbsp; NTA 4</span></span></li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:none; border-left:none; border-right:none; border-top:none; height:19px; vertical-align:bottom; white-space:nowrap\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li><span style=\"font-size:15px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">Basic Technician Certificate in Secretarial Studies (BTCSS) &ndash; NTA 4</span></span></li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:none; border-left:none; border-right:none; border-top:none; height:19px; vertical-align:bottom; white-space:nowrap\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li><span style=\"font-size:15px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">Basic Technician Certificate in Public Administration (BTCPA) &ndash; NTA 4</span></span></li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:none; border-left:none; border-right:none; border-top:none; height:19px; vertical-align:bottom; white-space:nowrap\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li><span style=\"font-size:15px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">Basic Technician Certificate in Human Resource Management (BTCHRM) &ndash; NTA 4</span></span></li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>','<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Academic Advising:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Assistance in course selection</li>\r\n		<li>Academic planning and progress tracking</li>\r\n		<li>Guidance on major and career choices</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Counseling Services:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Personal counseling</li>\r\n		<li>Career counseling</li>\r\n		<li>Mental health support</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Library Services:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Access to books, journals, and other resources</li>\r\n		<li>Research assistance and guidance</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Tutoring and Academic Support:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Peer tutoring services</li>\r\n		<li>Writing centers</li>\r\n		<li>Supplemental instruction programs</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Career Services:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Resume writing and interview preparation</li>\r\n		<li>Job search assistance</li>\r\n		<li>Career fairs and networking events</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Health Services:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Basic medical care</li>\r\n		<li>Counseling on health and wellness</li>\r\n		<li>Immunization and preventive health services</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>','<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Classrooms and Lecture Halls:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Equipped with audio-visual aids for effective teaching and learning.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Libraries:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Access to a collection of books, journals, and electronic resources.</li>\r\n		<li>Quiet study areas and collaborative spaces.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Laboratories:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Science labs for physics, chemistry, biology, etc.</li>\r\n		<li>Computer labs for programming, research, and general use.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Auditoriums and Theaters:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Spaces for large lectures, presentations, performances, and events.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Recreational Areas:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Sports fields, courts, and facilities for various sports.</li>\r\n		<li>Gyms and fitness centers.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Housing and Residential Facilities:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>On-campus dormitories or housing options.</li>\r\n		<li>Common areas and lounges for residents.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Dining Halls and Cafeterias:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Food services providing meals for students.</li>\r\n		<li>Options for different dietary preferences.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Student Centers:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Central hub for student activities and services.</li>\r\n		<li>Meeting rooms, event spaces, and student organization offices.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Health and Wellness Centers:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Medical clinics for basic healthcare.</li>\r\n		<li>Counseling services for mental health support.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>','<p><strong><u>Contacts</u></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Campus Director</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Tanzania Public Service College</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>P.O Box 1207</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Mbeya</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Phone<a name=\"_GoBack\"></a></em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Fax +255-252502627</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>E-mail: mbeya@tpsc.go.tz</em></p>','mbeya-campus','Kampasi ya Mbeya','Mbeya Campus','2024-01-11 07:18:47','2024-01-11 04:18:47'),(7,'<p><strong>Kampasi ya Tabora kwa Ufupi</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Chuo cha Utumishi wa Umma Tanzania (TPSC) Kampasi ya Tabora kilichokuwa kikijulikana kwa jina la Chuo cha Uhazili Tabora ni Kampasi ya pili ya zamani baada ya Kampasi ya Dar es Salaam kilichokuwa kikijulikana kama Chuo cha Mafunzo ya Utumishi wa Serikali. Chuo cha Uhazili Tabora kilianzishwa ili kujaza pengo la upungufu wa watumishi wa Ofisini na hasa Wahazili baada ya kupata Uhuru Tanzania. Ujenzi wa Chuo ulianza Septemba 1970 na kukamilika na kuanza kufanya kazi Oktoba, 1973. Chuo hiki kimekuwa na mabweni manne ya wanafunzi 600, wanaume 300 na wanawake 300 na maeneo ya michezo na burudani.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Mwaka 2000 Chuo cha Uhazili Tabora na Chuo cha Mafunzo cha Utumishi wa Serikali viliunda Chuo cha Utumishi wa Umma Tanzania kwa Sheria ya Wakala za Serikali Na. ya 2000.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Wakati wa kuanzishwa kwake ilikuwa na mihula miwili ya wiki 21 kwa mwaka, hasa kutilia mkazo Mafunzo ya awali na Mafunzo tarajali ya Uhazili na wakufunzi 29 tu. Hivi sasa Kampasi hii ina zaidi ya kozi 5, na wakufunzi wa kudumu 23 na wa muda 21 na Zaidi ya wanafunzi 2563 wanachukua program za Cheti na Diploma.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><em><u>Tuko wapi?</u></em></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Chuo cha Utumishi wa Umma Tanzania Kampasi ya Tabora kipo Mtaa wa Itetemya, Kata ya Kanyenye Manispaa ya Tabora mkabala na Makao makuu ya&nbsp; Polisi mkoa wa Tabora.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','<p>The following programmes are offered at Tabora Campus;</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Uhazili (NTAL Level 4 to NTA Level 6)</li>\r\n	<li>Utunzaji Kumbukumbu, Nyaraka, na Taarifa (NTAL Level 4 to NTA Level 6)</li>\r\n	<li>Menejimenti ya Rasilimali watu (NTAL Level 4 to NTA Level 6)</li>\r\n</ol>','<p><strong>Huduma za Malazi</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>-----</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Huduma za Afya</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>-----</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Dawati la Jinsia</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>-----</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Ushauri Nasaha</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>-----</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Serikali ya Wanafunzi</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>-----</p>','<p><strong>Madarasa</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>----</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Maabara za Upigaji Chapa</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>----</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Maabara za Kompyuta</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>----</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Maktaba</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>-----</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Mkurugenzi wa Kampasi</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Chuo cha Utumishi wa Umma Tanzania</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>S.L.P 329</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><strong>Tabora</strong></em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Simu: +255 26 260 5387</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Nukusi: +255 26 260 45 37</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Barua Pepe: <a>tabora@tpsc.go.tz</a></em></p>','<p><strong>Tabora Campus overview</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Chuo cha Utumishi wa Umma Tanzania (TPSC) Kampasi ya Tabora kilichokuwa kikijulikana kwa jina la Chuo cha Uhazili Tabora ni Kampasi ya pili ya zamani baada ya Kampasi ya Dar es Salaam kilichokuwa kikijulikana kama Chuo cha Mafunzo ya Utumishi wa Serikali. Chuo cha Uhazili Tabora kilianzishwa ili kujaza pengo la upungufu wa watumishi wa Ofisini na hasa Wahazili baada ya kupata Uhuru Tanzania. Ujenzi wa Chuo ulianza Septemba 1970 na kukamilika na kuanza kufanya kazi Oktoba, 1973. Chuo hiki kimekuwa na mabweni manne ya wanafunzi 600, wanaume 300 na wanawake 300 na maeneo ya michezo na burudani.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Mwaka 2000 Chuo cha Uhazili Tabora na Chuo cha Mafunzo cha Utumishi wa Serikali viliunda Chuo cha Utumishi wa Umma Tanzania kwa Sheria ya Wakala za Serikali Na. ya 2000.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Wakati wa kuanzishwa kwake ilikuwa na mihula miwili ya wiki 21 kwa mwaka, hasa kutilia mkazo Mafunzo ya awali na Mafunzo tarajali ya Uhazili na wakufunzi 29 tu. Hivi sasa Kampasi hii ina zaidi ya kozi 5, na wakufunzi wa kudumu 23 na wa muda 21 na Zaidi ya wanafunzi 2563 wanachukua program za Cheti na Diploma.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><em><u>Tuko wapi?</u></em></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Chuo cha Utumishi wa Umma Tanzania Kampasi ya Tabora kipo Mtaa wa Itetemya, Kata ya Kanyenye Manispaa ya Tabora mkabala na Makao makuu ya&nbsp; Polisi mkoa wa Tabora.</p>','<p>The following programmes are offered at Tabora Campus;</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Secretarial Studies (NTAL Level 4 to NTA Level 6)</li>\r\n	<li>Records, Archives and Information Management (NTAL Level 4 to NTA Level 6)</li>\r\n	<li>Human Resource Management (NTAL Level 4 to NTA Level 6)</li>\r\n</ol>','<p><strong>Accomodation</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>-----</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Health Service</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>-----</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Gender Issues</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>-----</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Guidance and Support</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>-----</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Students&#39; Government</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>-----</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Cafeteria Services</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>-----</p>','<p><strong>Madarasa</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>----</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Maabara za Upigaji Chapa</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>----</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Maabara za Kompyuta</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>----</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Maktaba</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>-----</p>','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Campus Director</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Tanzania Public Service College</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>P.O BOX 329,</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><strong>Tabora</strong></em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Phone: +255 26 260 5387</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Fax: +255 26 260 45 37</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Email: <a>tabora@tpsc.go.tz</a></em></p>','kampasi-ya-tabora','Kampasi ya Tabora','Tabora Campus','2024-01-11 07:18:20','2024-01-11 04:18:20'),(8,'<p>Chuo cha Utumishi wa Umma Kampasi ya Mtwara kilizinduliwa na Waziri Mkuu Mh. Mizengo Peter Pinda Tarehe 23 Novemba, 2009.Katika uzinduzi huo kampasi ilikuwa na jumla ya wanafunzi 261 na watumishi 7.Kwa sasa Kampasi ina wanafunzi zaidi ya 2000 na watumishi 57.Mwanzoni Kampasi hii ilikusudiwa kuhudumia Kanda na Mikoa mitatu (Mtwara, Lindi na Ruvuma) kwa sababu za mazingira yao ya kijografia na historia kimeshindwa kuvutia watu kusafiri kuja Dar es salaam na Tabora kwa ajili ya mafunzo zaidi. Kwa hiyo Kampasi ya Mtwara pamekuwa mahali pa kuanzia kwa watu wa Mikoa ya Kusini kujiunga na mafunzo ya elimu ya juu.Kwa sasa Kampasi ya Mtwara inatoa mafunzo kwa Mikoa ya Kusini pamoja na Mikoa yote ya Tanzania.Ina wanafunzi takribani kutoka kila Mkoa wa Tanzania.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Tuko wapi?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Kampasi ya Mtwara (TPSC) ipo sehemu yakusini ya Tanzania katika Mkoa wa Mtwara, eneo la Shangani Mashariki, karibu na Nyumba za Shirika la Nyumba Tanzania Shangani na Hospitali ya Tawi la Ndanda.Kama ukiwa Kituo Kikuu chaMabasi cha Mkoa au mahali kwengine kokote katika Mji wa Mtwara, Chukua Usafiri wa Bodaboda mwambie derive akupeleke &ldquo;Chuo cha Utumishi Mtwara&rdquo;</p>','<p>Utunzaji wa kumbukumbu......./.</p>','<p>1. Medical services&nbsp;<br />\r\nThe Campus has collaboration with nearby Health centers which provides clinical and health services. This nearby Health Centre&rsquo;s provides for referral cases to Ligula Regional Hospital and Southern Zone Referral Hospital where facilities for serious medication and surgical attention exist. Nevertheless, the campus encourages staff and students to join the National Health Insurance Fund (NHIF) which guarantees the medical treatment at the nearby health centers and regional hospital. Upon admission, all students are required to pay medical capitation fees and receive medical services based on these fees.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n2. Accommodation services&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Students are accommodated by nearby private hostels which are approved by the campus management. The list of private hostels and the contacts are normally attached with the admission letters.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3. Academic Support<br />\r\nThe campus utilizes opportunity to develop skills, knowledge and insights through well researched, designed competence-based programmes, resourced by highly qualified and registered CBET training providers. The campus has taken all measures to make sure that the information provided is current and accurate, in terms of staffing, curricula, course contents and teaching facilities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>5. Tanzania Public Service Student&rsquo;s Organization (TAPSSO)<br />\r\nFormal student activities are administered by the Tanzania Public Service Student&rsquo;s Organization (TAPSSO). TAPSSO is concerned with students&rsquo; academic, social and recreational activities. Every campus student is automatically a member of TAPSSO. Most of the students&rsquo; activities are organized by the student organization. The student organization addresses itself on aspects of representing students&rsquo; interest on various campus decision making bodies. TAPSSO under the leadership of its President is a formal active voice of students, within and outside the campus. Besides, under TAPSSO there are professional academic associations (affiliated to TAPSSO) such as religious, Environment protection, PCCB club, Ethics club as well as Campus choir.</p>','<p>1. Classrooms<br />\r\nThe campus has total of nine (9) classrooms, two (2) computer laboratories, one (1) typing room, and one (1) registry model.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. Campus Library<br />\r\nThe campus Library contains up-to-date book collections in the fields of Management, Administration, Secretarial studies, Records and Archive management, Law, ICT, and Statistics. The library currently comprises of about 2000 book volumes that cater for all the courses conducted at the campus. The library can accommodate about 80 readers at a time. The books stock is classified and arranged according to the Dewey Decimal Classification Scheme 22nd edition and catalogued according to the Anglo American Cataloguing Rules (AACR) 2nd edition Revised in 2002. The library produces Library Rules and Guide as may be required within an academic year. The Guide and rules are for distribution to fresh students during the orientation week and they are required to read and abide by them. Moreover, there is growing collection of e-library that accompanies some new books. This database is important because it provide more information in various subject areas.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3.Games and Sports<br />\r\nThe campus use nearby facilities for out-doors games such as football, basketball, netball and volleyball. The campus also has sports equipment such as balls for all mentioned games, jerseys, whistles, ball pumps, stop watches, corner flags, and nets of different games to mention few. Currently there are two appointed games tutors who organize and co-ordinate all games and sports activities for both staff and students in and out of the campus. Therefore, all students are expected and encouraged to have sports outfit.</p>','<p><em>Mkurugenzi wa Kampasi</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Chuo cha Utumishi wa Umma Tanzania</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>S.L.P 1051</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><em>Mtwara</em></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Simu:</em><em>&nbsp;</em>: +255 232 333300</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Nukushi</em><em>&nbsp;</em>+255 232 333300</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Barua Pepe:</em><em>&nbsp;</em>mtwara@tpsc.go.tz</p>','<p>TPSC Mtwara campus is a branch of Tanzania Public Service College which was officially inaugurated by the Prime Minister Honourable Mizengo Peter Pinda on the 23rd November 2009. At its inauguration, it had a total of 261 students with 7 staffs. Currently, it has over 2,000 students with 57 staffs. Initially the campus was aimed at catering the three southern zonal regions (Mtwara, Lindi and Ruvuma) as their geographical and historical background failed to attract people travelling to Dar es Salaam and Tabora to pursue their further studies. Hence Mtwara Campus has been a stepping stone for southern regions people to join to higher studies.<br />\r\nIn the mean time, TPSC Mtwara is not only serving the southern regions but all regions in Tanzania. It has students comming from almost every regions in Tanzania.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Where are We?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>TPSC Mtwara campus is located at the southern part of Tanzania, in Mtwara region, at the Shangani East area, near National housing houses Shangani and Ndanda branch hospital. If you are at the main regional bus stand (or any where around Mtwara town), pick a Bodaboda and ask the driver to bring you to &quot;Chuo cha utumishi Mtwara&quot;</p>','<p>Records and archaive management........</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','<p>1. Medical services&nbsp;<br />\r\nThe Campus has collaboration with nearby Health centers which provides clinical and health services. This nearby Health Centre&rsquo;s provides for referral cases to Ligula Regional Hospital and Southern Zone Referral Hospital where facilities for serious medication and surgical attention exist. Nevertheless, the campus encourages staff and students to join the National Health Insurance Fund (NHIF) which guarantees the medical treatment at the nearby health centers and regional hospital. Upon admission, all students are required to pay medical capitation fees and receive medical services based on these fees.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n2. Accommodation services&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Students are accommodated by nearby private hostels which are approved by the campus management. The list of private hostels and the contacts are normally attached with the admission letters.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3. Academic Support<br />\r\nThe campus utilizes opportunity to develop skills, knowledge and insights through well researched, designed competence-based programmes, resourced by highly qualified and registered CBET training providers. The campus has taken all measures to make sure that the information provided is current and accurate, in terms of staffing, curricula, course contents and teaching facilities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>5. Tanzania Public Service Student&rsquo;s Organization (TAPSSO)<br />\r\nFormal student activities are administered by the Tanzania Public Service Student&rsquo;s Organization (TAPSSO). TAPSSO is concerned with students&rsquo; academic, social and recreational activities. Every campus student is automatically a member of TAPSSO. Most of the students&rsquo; activities are organized by the student organization. The student organization addresses itself on aspects of representing students&rsquo; interest on various campus decision making bodies. TAPSSO under the leadership of its President is a formal active voice of students, within and outside the campus. Besides, under TAPSSO there are professional academic associations (affiliated to TAPSSO) such as religious, Environment protection, PCCB club, Ethics club as well as Campus choir.</p>','<p>1. Classrooms<br />\r\nThe campus has total of nine (9) classrooms, two (2) computer laboratories, one (1) typing room, and one (1) registry model.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. Campus Library<br />\r\nThe campus Library contains up-to-date book collections in the fields of Management, Administration, Secretarial studies, Records and Archive management, Law, ICT, and Statistics. The library currently comprises of about 2000 book volumes that cater for all the courses conducted at the campus. The library can accommodate about 80 readers at a time. The books stock is classified and arranged according to the Dewey Decimal Classification Scheme 22nd edition and catalogued according to the Anglo American Cataloguing Rules (AACR) 2nd edition Revised in 2002. The library produces Library Rules and Guide as may be required within an academic year. The Guide and rules are for distribution to fresh students during the orientation week and they are required to read and abide by them. Moreover, there is growing collection of e-library that accompanies some new books. This database is important because it provide more information in various subject areas.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3.Games and Sports<br />\r\nThe campus use nearby facilities for out-doors games such as football, basketball, netball and volleyball. The campus also has sports equipment such as balls for all mentioned games, jerseys, whistles, ball pumps, stop watches, corner flags, and nets of different games to mention few. Currently there are two appointed games tutors who organize and co-ordinate all games and sports activities for both staff and students in and out of the campus. Therefore, all students are expected and encouraged to have sports outfit.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>,&nbsp;</p>','<p>Campus Director</p>\r\n\r\n<p>TPSC Mtwara Campus</p>\r\n\r\n<p>P.O.Box 1051</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Mtwara</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Phone: +255 232 333300</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Fax: +255 232 333300</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Email: mtwara@tpsc.go.tz</p>','mtwara-campus','Kampasi ya Mtwara','Mtwara Campus','2024-01-11 07:17:19','2024-01-11 04:17:19'),(9,'<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The Global Learning Centre (GLC) is a Directorate of Tanzania Public Service College (TPSC). It is a capacity building centre with wide-range capacity building interventions that include; Leadership and Managerial Skills development, Board Governance and Leadership, Fraud investigation, Fundamentals of Regulation in Utility Services and other regulatory areas (water, oil, electricity and Gas, weather), Change Management, Transformation Leadership, Financial management, Project management, Team Building and Coaching, Human Resource management, Counselling and Guidance, and Enterprise Risk Management. GLC is also a member of the Global Development<br />\r\nLearning Network (GDLN) which is a partnership of over 120 recognised global institutions (ffiliates) in over 80 countries that collaborates in the design of customised learning solutions for individuals and organisations working in development.</p>','<p>.</p>','<p>.</p>','<p>-.</p>','<p>.</p>','<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The Global Learning Centre (GLC) is a Directorate of Tanzania Public Service College (TPSC). It is a capacity building centre with wide-range capacity building interventions that include; Leadership and Managerial Skills development, Board Governance and Leadership, Fraud investigation, Fundamentals of Regulation in Utility Services and other regulatory areas (water, oil, electricity and Gas, weather), Change Management, Transformation Leadership, Financial management, Project management, Team Building and Coaching, Human Resource management, Counselling and Guidance, and Enterprise Risk Management. GLC is also a member of the Global Development<br />\r\nLearning Network (GDLN) which is a partnership of over 120 recognised global institutions (ffiliates) in over 80 countries that collaborates in the design of customised learning solutions for individuals and organisations working in development.</p>','<p>.</p>','<p>.</p>','<p>.</p>','<p>.</p>','global-learning-section','Kituo cha Mafunzo kwa Njia ya Mtandandao','Global Learning Section','2024-01-11 07:16:50','2024-01-11 04:16:50'),(10,'<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Tanzania Public Service College &ndash; Singida Campus is one of the six (6) Campuses of the Tanzania Public Service College (TPSC). The Campus was established in July 2011, being the fourth campus to be established among the six campuses of TPSC. Its establishment was a result of instructions issued by Prime Minister Hon. Mizengo Pinda on 23rd November 2009 during inauguration of Tanzania Public Service College Mtwara Campus. Singida Campus is located along airport road in Mandewa Ward at Singida Municipality &ndash;Singida Region.&nbsp;</p>','<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Footlight MT Light&quot;,serif\">Kampasi ya Singida ipo Barabara ya Uwanja wa Ndege, Kata ya Mandewa -Manispaa ya Singida. Kampasi ya Singida inatoa kozi mbalimbali kuanzia ngazi ya astashahada na stashahada. Miongoni mwa kozi hizo ni pamoja na astashahada ya utunzaji wa kumbukumbu, astashahada ya uhazili, astashahada ya menejimenti ya rasilimaliwatu na astashahada ya utawala wa umma (NTA,4) pamoja na&nbsp; stashahada ya utunzaji wa kumbukumbu, stashahada ya uhazili, stashahada ya menejimenti ya rasilimaliwatu na stashahada ya utawala wa umma (NTA 5&amp; 6). Aidha, Kampasi ya Singida ni kituo cha mafunzo ya muda mfupi kwa watumishi wa umma, shauri za kitaalamu na ni kituo&nbsp; cha&nbsp; mafunzo na mitihani kwa watumishi wa umma</span></span></p>','<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Footlight MT Light&quot;,serif\">Ili kuwasaidia wanachuo kupata ujuzi kwa lengo la kukuza weledi wao na maendeleo ya taaluma&nbsp; zao&nbsp; katika fani mbalimbali walizochagua , kampasi ya Singida ipo katika mazingira mazuri ambayo yana-:</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Footlight MT Light&quot;,serif\">Huduma za&nbsp; uhakika za&nbsp; kifedha na chakula zinazotolewa na taasisi mbalimbali za kifedha na chakula ili &nbsp;kusaidia upatikanaji rahisi wa huduma za fedha na chakula kwa gharama nafuu</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Footlight MT Light&quot;,serif\">Hali ya hewa nzuri&nbsp; inayofungamanishwa&nbsp; na mazingira mazuri ya kujisomea&nbsp; na kujifunza </span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Footlight MT Light&quot;,serif\">Huduma nzuri za hosteli na malazi zinazopatikana kwa bei rahisi. Kampasi inatoa huduma za hosteli zinazopatikana ndani na nje ya chuo. Hosteli za nje ya kampasi zinapatikana kwa kushirikiana na wamiliki binafsi lakini chini ya usimamizi wa menejimenti ya Kampasi.&nbsp; Ghrama za hostei kwa muhula ni kati ya Tsh. 150,000-200,000 kutegemeana na ubora &nbsp;wa hosteli husika </span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Footlight MT Light&quot;,serif\">Huduma nzuri za&nbsp; afya ambazo hutolewa kupitia vituo vya kutolea huduma za afya vinavyomilikiwa na serikali na taasisi binafsi&nbsp; hususan Hospitali ya Manispaa ya Singida, Hospitali ya Rufaa ya Mkoa , Kituo cha afya cha Tumaini, Kituo cha Afya MICO n,k. Vituo vyote hivi vya kutolea huduma za afya vinafikika kirahisi, vinatoa huduma bora&nbsp; na vipo karibu na chuo. </span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Footlight MT Light&quot;,serif\">Huduma za kuabudu kwa dini zote na madhehebu yote. Kampasi ya Singida ipo karibu kabisa na nyumba mbalimbali za kuabudia (makanisa na misikiti) kwa wanachuo wa dini zote. Aidha, Kampasi ya Singida imeruhusu wanachuo kutumia ukumbi wa chuo kwa ajili ya kuabudia pale unapohitajika</span><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Footlight MT Light&quot;,serif\">.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Footlight MT Light&quot;,serif\">Huduma za viwanja vya michezo mbalimbali ili kuwapa wanachuo pamoja na walimu wao &nbsp;fursa ya kushiriki kwenye michezo mbalimbali ili kuimarisha afya zao &nbsp;na kuboresha maendeleo ya taaluma zao. Baadhi ya viwanja vya&nbsp; michezo vilivyopo ni pamoja na viwanja vya mpira wa miguu, mpira wa pete&nbsp; na mpira wa wavu </span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Footlight MT Light&quot;,serif\">Huduma za bima za&nbsp; afya ambazo zinatolewa kwa ushirikiano na Mfuko wa Taifa wa Bima ya Afya (NHIF) ili kurahisisha upatikanaji wa afya bora na kwa wakati kwa wanachuo. </span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Footlight MT Light&quot;,serif\">Huduma za ushauri&nbsp; hususan ushauri kuhusu mambo ya kiafya,&nbsp; kitaaluma, kiuchumi na kifedha, na kisaikolojia&nbsp; hutolewa kwa wanachuo wenye uhitaji na wanachuo wote kwa ujumla </span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Footlight MT Light&quot;,serif\">Huduma nzuri za ulinzi na usalama wakati wote hivyo kuwasaidia wanachuo kujifunza pasipo hofu zozote za kiusalama.</span></span></span></li>\r\n</ol>','<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Footlight MT Light&quot;,serif\">Kampasi ya Singida inatoa huduma zake za kitaaluma kupitia kwenye madarasa ya kisasa na yanayopitisha hewa ya kutosha, maabara za kisasa za kuchapia, maabara za kisasa za komputa, maktaba nzuri yenye vitabu vya kisasa, mtandao wa kutosha kuwezesha wanachuo kujitafutia mahitaji yao ya kujifunzia kwenye vyanzo mbalimbali, n.k. Aidha, Kampasi ina watumishi ( Walimu na Wasiowalimu) wanaojituma, wenye weledi, hamasa na wenye vipaji vya kutosha kufanya kazi ya kuwajengea uwezo wanachuo katika Nyanja tofauti tofauti kwa utiifu na uaminifu mkubwa. &nbsp;</span></span></span></p>','<p><em>Mkurugenzi wa Kampasi</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Chuo cha Utumishi wa Umma Tanzania</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>S.L.P 1534</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><em>Singida</em></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><em>Simu:</em></strong><em>&nbsp;</em><em>+255 26 2502933/3082</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><em>Nukushi</em></strong><em>&nbsp;</em><em>+255 26 250 3082</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><em>Barua Pepe:</em></strong><em>&nbsp;</em><em>singida@tpsc.go.tz</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Footlight MT Light&quot;,serif\">&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>','<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Footlight MT Light&quot;,serif\">Kampasi ya Singida ni miongoni mwa Kampasi sita za Chuo cha Utumishi wa Umma Tanzania.&nbsp; Kampasi ya Singida&nbsp;&nbsp; ilianzishwa rasmi Mwezi wa Saba (7) mwaka 2011 ikiwa ni kampasi ya nne kuanzishwa kati ya Kampasi sita za Chuo.&nbsp; Kuanzishwa kwa Kampasi ya Singida ni utekelezaji wa maelekezo aliyoyatoa aliyekuwa Waziri Mkuu </span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Footlight MT Light&quot;,serif\">Mh. Mizengo Pinda tarehe 23 Novemba, 2009 wakati akifungua kampasi ya Mtwara. Kamapasi ya Singida ipo Barabara ya Uwanja wa Ndege, Kata ya Mandewa -Manispaa ya Singida</span></span>.</p>','<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The Campus offers a wide range of programmes from Certificate to Diploma levels. The courses offered include Basic Technician Certificate in Secretarial Studies (BTCSS) &ndash; NTA 4; Basic Technician Certificate in Records Management (BTCRM) - NTA 4; Basic Technician Certificate in Human Resource Management (BTCHRM) &ndash; NTA 4; Basic Technician Certificate in Public Administration (BTCPA) &ndash; NTA 4; Ordinary Diploma in Secretarial Studies (ODSS) &ndash; NTA 5 &amp; 6; Ordinary Diploma in Records Management (ODRM) (NTA 5 &amp; 6); Ordinary Diploma in Public Administration (ODPA) &ndash; NTA 5 &amp; 6 and Ordinary Diploma in Human Resource Management (ODHRM)&ndash;NTA 5 &amp; 6. Likewise, the Campus offers short courses and consultant services to different stakeholders in the public and private sector. It is also the centre for coordinating and conducting Public Service Examinations (PSE) to public servants. Singida Campus follows Competence Based Education Training (CBET) curricula and positions itself to practice all its endeavors at the highest level of standards</p>','<p style=\"text-align:justify\">To enable students acquire necessary skills for professionalism and career development in different areas of specialization the campus has ensured-:</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">a)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Reliable catering and banking services to facilitate &nbsp;availability of food and banking services at affordable cost<br />\r\nb)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Good climatic condition surrounded by greenish environment that makes learning and studying environment conducive.&nbsp;<br />\r\nc)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;The accommodation services: The campus offers a range of quality accommodation services both on-campus and off-campus. Off campus accommodation services are handled in collaboration with private owners of hostels but under the management and control of Campus management. The services are charged at the rate of TZS. 150,000-200,000/= per &nbsp;semester&nbsp;<br />\r\nd)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Government and private owned health facilities including Singida Regional Referral Hospital, Singida Municipal Hospital, Tumaini Health Centre and MICO Health Centre that provide high quality, responsive and sustainable health services are all located nearby the Campus.<br />\r\ne)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Religious facilities including churches for Christian students and Mosque for Muslims students are available for enhancing students&rsquo; spiritual life. Apart from that, campus provides building for worshipping services for all Christians and Muslims students who need extra religious services.<br />\r\nf)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Sports and games facilities that aim to promote overall health and mental ability of the students and teachers. Sports facilities available include football pitches, netball, and volleyball among others.&nbsp;<br />\r\ng)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Health Insurance services which are provided in collaboration with National Health Insurance Funds (NHIF) are ensured to students for ease and quality acquisition of health services at the affordable cost.<br />\r\nh)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Counseling services that aims to offer services targeting health related concerns; academic (teaching and learning) concerns; psycho-social concerns; economic and financial concerns and other personal concerns. Likewise, the section commensurate with provision of high-quality services that nurture students to engage in academic and social development effectively.</p>','<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The campus provides academic services in well ventilated and modern classrooms, laboratories (both typing and computer laboratories) with a well-equipped library that contain modern and current books, internet and learning facilities. Teaching and learning activities are facilitated by well and highly qualified, motivated, committed and talented facilitators who are eager to serve the customers with high level of loyalty and integrity.&nbsp;</p>','<p><em>Campus Director,</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Tanzania Public Service College</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>P.O. Box 1534</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Singida</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Phone: +255 26 2502933/3082</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Fax: +255 26 250 3082</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Email: singida@tpsc.go.tz</em></p>','singida-campus','Kampasi  ya Singida','Singida Campus','2024-01-17 14:36:46','2024-01-17 11:36:46');
