ponsibility changes</li>\r\n	<li>life styles</li>\r\n</ol>','<ol>\r\n	<li>Afya</li>\r\n	<li>uwekezaji</li>\r\n	<li>mabadiliko ya majukumu</li>\r\n	<li>mazoezi</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','<p>Kustaafu kwa furaha</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Kujiandaa Kisaikolojia kwenye majukumu mapya</p>\r\n\r\n<p>kuwaandaa wastaafu kuendelea na maisha yao vizuri baada kustaafu</p>','<p>Kustaafu kwa furaha</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Kujiandaa Kisaikolojia kwenye majukumu mapya</p>\r\n\r\n<p>kuwaandaa wastaafu kuendelea na maisha yao vizuri baada kustaafu</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','<p>Shakiru Abdulkarim</p>','<p>Shakiru Abdulkarim</p>','',12,'2023-12-15 07:15:26','2023-12-15 07:15:26',2),(15,'<p>Basic Computer Applications typically cover a range of fundamental concepts and skills related to using computers and common software. Here are the basic topics that may be included in a Basic Computer Applications course:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Introduction to Computers:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Definition and components of a computer system</li>\r\n		<li>Understanding hardware and software</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Operating Systems:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Basics of operating systems (e.g., Windows, macOS, Linux)</li>\r\n		<li>File management and navigation</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Word Processing:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Using word processing software (e.g., Microsoft Word, Google Docs)</li>\r\n		<li>Creating, editing, and formatting documents</li>\r\n		<li>Working with tables and images</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Spreadsheets:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Introduction to spreadsheet software (e.g., Microsoft Excel, Google Sheets)</li>\r\n		<li>Creating and formatting spreadsheets</li>\r\n		<li>Formulas and functions for calculations</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Presentations:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Creating and delivering presentations</li>\r\n		<li>Using presentation software (e.g., Microsoft PowerPoint, Google Slides)</li>\r\n		<li>Incorporating multimedia elements</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Internet Basics:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Web browsers and navigation</li>\r\n		<li>Understanding URLs and websites</li>\r\n		<li>Internet safety and security</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Email and Communication:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Using email for communication</li>\r\n		<li>Attachments and email etiquette</li>\r\n		<li>Online communication tools (e.g., messaging apps)</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Basic Computer Security:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Password management</li>\r\n		<li>Antivirus software and malware protection</li>\r\n		<li>Safe internet browsing practices</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>File Management and Backup:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Organizing files and folders</li>\r\n		<li>Creating backups and restoring data</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Introduction to Software Applications:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Overview of common software applications (e.g., Adobe Acrobat, image editing tools)</li>\r\n		<li>Installing and uninstalling software</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Computer Hardware Awareness:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Understanding computer hardware components (CPU, RAM, storage)</li>\r\n		<li>Basic troubleshooting and maintenance</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Cloud Computing:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Basics of cloud storage and services</li>\r\n		<li>Uploading and sharing files using cloud platforms</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Collaborative Tools:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Introduction to collaborative platforms (e.g., Google Workspace, Microsoft Teams)</li>\r\n		<li>Online document collaboration</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Basic Programming Concepts:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Introduction to programming logic</li>\r\n		<li>Understanding algorithms and pseudocode</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Ethical and Social Implications:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Digital citizenship</li>\r\n		<li>Ethical use of technology and information</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Emerging Technologies:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Introduction to emerging technologies (e.g., AI, IoT)</li>\r\n		<li>Future trends in computing</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>','<p>Basic Computer Applications typically cover a range of fundamental concepts and skills related to using computers and common software. Here are the basic topics that may be included in a Basic Computer Applications course:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Introduction to Computers:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Definition and components of a computer system</li>\r\n		<li>Understanding hardware and software</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Operating Systems:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Basics of operating systems (e.g., Windows, macOS, Linux)</li>\r\n		<li>File management and navigation</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Word Processing:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Using word processing software (e.g., Microsoft Word, Google Docs)</li>\r\n		<li>Creating, editing, and formatting documents</li>\r\n		<li>Working with tables and images</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Spreadsheets:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Introduction to spreadsheet software (e.g., Microsoft Excel, Google Sheets)</li>\r\n		<li>Creating and formatting spreadsheets</li>\r\n		<li>Formulas and functions for calculations</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Presentations:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Creating and delivering presentations</li>\r\n		<li>Using presentation software (e.g., Microsoft PowerPoint, Google Slides)</li>\r\n		<li>Incorporating multimedia elements</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Internet Basics:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Web browsers and navigation</li>\r\n		<li>Understanding URLs and websites</li>\r\n		<li>Internet safety and security</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Email and Communication:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Using email for communication</li>\r\n		<li>Attachments and email etiquette</li>\r\n		<li>Online communication tools (e.g., messaging apps)</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Basic Computer Security:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Password management</li>\r\n		<li>Antivirus software and malware protection</li>\r\n		<li>Safe internet browsing practices</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>File Management and Backup:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Organizing files and folders</li>\r\n		<li>Creating backups and restoring data</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Introduction to Software Applications:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Overview of common software applications (e.g., Adobe Acrobat, image editing tools)</li>\r\n		<li>Installing and uninstalling software</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Computer Hardware Awareness:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Understanding computer hardware components (CPU, RAM, storage)</li>\r\n		<li>Basic troubleshooting and maintenance</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Cloud Computing:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Basics of cloud storage and services</li>\r\n		<li>Uploading and sharing files using cloud platforms</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Collaborative Tools:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Introduction to collaborative platforms (e.g., Google Workspace, Microsoft Teams)</li>\r\n		<li>Online document collaboration</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Basic Programming Concepts:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Introduction to programming logic</li>\r\n		<li>Understanding algorithms and pseudocode</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Ethical and Social Implications:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Digital citizenship</li>\r\n		<li>Ethical use of technology and information</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Emerging Technologies:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Introduction to emerging technologies (e.g., AI, IoT)</li>\r\n		<li>Future trends in computing</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>','<p>Basic Computer Application courses are designed for individuals who are new to using computers or those who want to enhance their basic computer skills. The audience for these courses is typically diverse and may include:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Beginners and Novices:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Individuals who have little or no experience with computers.</li>\r\n		<li>Those who are unfamiliar with basic software applications and operating systems.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Adult Learners:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Adults who are returning to education or the workforce and need to acquire or refresh basic computer skills.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Senior Citizens:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Older individuals who are interested in learning how to use computers for communication, information retrieval, and basic tasks.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Job Seekers:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Individuals looking to improve their employability by acquiring fundamental computer skills required in many workplaces.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Students:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>High school or college students who need to develop basic computer proficiency for academic purposes.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Small Business Owners:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Entrepreneurs and small business owners who want to manage basic computer tasks, such as word processing, spreadsheet calculations, and email communication.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Parents and Caregivers:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Individuals responsible for children or family members who want to stay connected through digital communication or assist with educational technology.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Technologically Inexperienced Professionals:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Professionals in fields that traditionally have not required extensive computer use but are now transitioning to more digital workflows.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Non-technical Professionals:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Individuals in non-technical professions who need basic computer skills for tasks such as documentation, presentations, and data analysis.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Community and Social Groups:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Members of community organizations or social groups seeking to improve their computer literacy for various purposes.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Global Audience:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Individuals from diverse backgrounds and cultures who may have limited exposure to computer technology.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>','<p>Basic Computer Application courses are designed for individuals who are new to using computers or those who want to enhance their basic computer skills. The audience for these courses is typically diverse and may include:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Beginners and Novices:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Individuals who have little or no experience with computers.</li>\r\n		<li>Those who are unfamiliar with basic software applications and operating systems.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Adult Learners:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Adults who are returning to education or the workforce and need to acquire or refresh basic computer skills.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Senior Citizens:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Older individuals who are interested in learning how to use computers for communication, information retrieval, and basic tasks.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Job Seekers:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Individuals looking to improve their employability by acquiring fundamental computer skills required in many workplaces.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Students:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>High school or college students who need to develop basic computer proficiency for academic purposes.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Small Business Owners:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Entrepreneurs and small business owners who want to manage basic computer tasks, such as word processing, spreadsheet calculations, and email communication.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Parents and Caregivers:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Individuals responsible for children or family members who want to stay connected through digital communication or assist with educational technology.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Technologically Inexperienced Professionals:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Professionals in fields that traditionally have not required extensive computer use but are now transitioning to more digital workflows.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Non-technical Professionals:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Individuals in non-technical professions who need basic computer skills for tasks such as documentation, presentations, and data analysis.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Community and Social Groups:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Members of community organizations or social groups seeking to improve their computer literacy for various purposes.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Global Audience:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Individuals from diverse backgrounds and cultures who may have limited exposure to computer technology.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>','<p>A Computer Application course provides an overview of essential computer skills and applications commonly used in various settings. The course aims to equip participants with practical knowledge and proficiency in fundamental software tools. Below is a general overview of topics that may be covered in a Computer Application course:</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Module 1: Introduction to Computers and Operating Systems</h3>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Computer Basics:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Components of a computer system</li>\r\n		<li>Input and output devices</li>\r\n		<li>Storage devices</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Operating Systems:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Overview of operating systems (e.g., Windows, macOS, Linux)</li>\r\n		<li>File management and navigation</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3>Module 2: Word Processing</h3>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Introduction to Word Processing:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Word processing software (e.g., Microsoft Word, Google Docs)</li>\r\n		<li>Creating, editing, and formatting documents</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Document Elements:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Styles, fonts, and formatting options</li>\r\n		<li>Headers, footers, and page layout</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Tables and Graphics:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Creating and formatting tables</li>\r\n		<li>Inserting and manipulating images and graphics</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3>Module 3: Spreadsheets</h3>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Introduction to Spreadsheets:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Spreadsheet software (e.g., Microsoft Excel, Google Sheets)</li>\r\n		<li>Creating and formatting spreadsheets</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Formulas and Functions:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Basic mathematical operations</li>\r\n		<li>Common formulas and functions</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Charts and Graphs:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Creating visual representations of data</li>\r\n		<li>Customizing charts</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3>Module 4: Presentations</h3>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Introduction to Presentations:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Presentation software (e.g., Microsoft PowerPoint, Google Slides)</li>\r\n		<li>Creating and editing slides</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Slide Design and Layout:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Themes, layouts, and formatting options</li>\r\n		<li>Adding multimedia elements</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Presentation Delivery:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Rehearsing and delivering presentations</li>\r\n		<li>Incorporating speaker notes and transitions</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3>Module 5: Internet and Communication</h3>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Internet Basics:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Web browsers, search engines, and URLs</li>\r\n		<li>Safe internet browsing practices</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Email Communication:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Sending and receiving emails</li>\r\n		<li>Email etiquette and best practices</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3>Module 6: Basic Computer Security</h3>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Password Management:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Creating strong passwords</li>\r\n		<li>Password best practices</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Antivirus and Malware Protection:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Understanding and using antivirus software</li>\r\n		<li>Recognizing and avoiding malware</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3>Module 7: File Management and Backup</h3>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Organizing Files and Folders:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Creating a file hierarchy</li>\r\n		<li>Renaming and moving files</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Data Backup:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Importance of data backup</li>\r\n		<li>Creating backups and restoring data</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3>Module 8: Practical Applications and Projects</h3>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Hands-On Projects:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Applying learned skills in real-world scenarios</li>\r\n		<li>Creating documents, spreadsheets, and presentations</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Troubleshooting Basics:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Basic problem-solving strategies</li>\r\n		<li>Common issues and solutions</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3>Module 9: Emerging Technologies</h3>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li><strong>Introduction to Emerging Technologies:</strong>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Overview of current and future trends (e.g., AI, IoT)</li>\r\n		<li>Exploring new technologies</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3>Module 10: Review and Assessment</h3>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Course Review:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Recap of key concepts and skills</li>\r\n		<li>Q&amp;A and clarification of doubts</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Assessment:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Evaluation through quizzes, assignments, or a final project</li>\r\n		<li>Certification for successful completion</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>This course structure provides participants with a well-rounded understanding of basic computer applications and prepares them for practical use in both personal and professional contexts. The hands-on projects and practical applications ensure that participants gain valuable experience applying the skills they&#39;ve learned.</p>','<p>A Computer Application course provides an overview of essential computer skills and applications commonly used in various settings. The course aims to equip participants with practical knowledge and proficiency in fundamental software tools. Below is a general overview of topics that may be covered in a Computer Application course:</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Module 1: Introduction to Computers and Operating Systems</h3>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Computer Basics:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Components of a computer system</li>\r\n		<li>Input and output devices</li>\r\n		<li>Storage devices</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Operating Systems:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Overview of operating systems (e.g., Windows, macOS, Linux)</li>\r\n		<li>File management and navigation</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3>Module 2: Word Processing</h3>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Introduction to Word Processing:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Word processing software (e.g., Microsoft Word, Google Docs)</li>\r\n		<li>Creating, editing, and formatting documents</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Document Elements:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Styles, fonts, and formatting options</li>\r\n		<li>Headers, footers, and page layout</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Tables and Graphics:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Creating and formatting tables</li>\r\n		<li>Inserting and manipulating images and graphics</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3>Module 3: Spreadsheets</h3>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Introduction to Spreadsheets:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Spreadsheet software (e.g., Microsoft Excel, Google Sheets)</li>\r\n		<li>Creating and formatting spreadsheets</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Formulas and Functions:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Basic mathematical operations</li>\r\n		<li>Common formulas and functions</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Charts and Graphs:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Creating visual representations of data</li>\r\n		<li>Customizing charts</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3>Module 4: Presentations</h3>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Introduction to Presentations:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Presentation software (e.g., Microsoft PowerPoint, Google Slides)</li>\r\n		<li>Creating and editing slides</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Slide Design and Layout:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Themes, layouts, and formatting options</li>\r\n		<li>Adding multimedia elements</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Presentation Delivery:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Rehearsing and delivering presentations</li>\r\n		<li>Incorporating speaker notes and transitions</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3>Module 5: Internet and Communication</h3>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Internet Basics:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Web browsers, search engines, and URLs</li>\r\n		<li>Safe internet browsing practices</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Email Communication:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Sending and receiving emails</li>\r\n		<li>Email etiquette and best practices</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3>Module 6: Basic Computer Security</h3>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Password Management:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Creating strong passwords</li>\r\n		<li>Password best practices</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Antivirus and Malware Protection:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Understanding and using antivirus software</li>\r\n		<li>Recognizing and avoiding malware</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3>Module 7: File Management and Backup</h3>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Organizing Files and Folders:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Creating a file hierarchy</li>\r\n		<li>Renaming and moving files</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Data Backup:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Importance of data backup</li>\r\n		<li>Creating backups and restoring data</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3>Module 8: Practical Applications and Projects</h3>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Hands-On Projects:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Applying learned skills in real-world scenarios</li>\r\n		<li>Creating documents, spreadsheets, and presentations</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Troubleshooting Basics:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Basic problem-solving strategies</li>\r\n		<li>Common issues and solutions</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3>Module 9: Emerging Technologies</h3>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li><strong>Introduction to Emerging Technologies:</strong>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Overview of current and future trends (e.g., AI, IoT)</li>\r\n		<li>Exploring new technologies</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3>Module 10: Review and Assessment</h3>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Course Review:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Recap of key concepts and skills</li>\r\n		<li>Q&amp;A and clarification of doubts</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Assessment:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Evaluation through quizzes, assignments, or a final project</li>\r\n		<li>Certification for successful completion</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>This course structure provides participants with a well-rounded understanding of basic computer applications and prepares them for practical use in both personal and professional contexts. The hands-on projects and practical applications ensure that participants gain valuable experience applying the skills they&#39;ve learned.</p>','<p>A Basic Computer Application course offers numerous benefits for individuals who participate, regardless of their background or current skill level. Here are some key advantages:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Enhanced Employability:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Acquiring basic computer skills enhances employability in various industries. Many job roles require at least a fundamental understanding of common software applications and computer usage.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Access to Educational Resources:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Basic computer skills enable individuals to access educational resources online, enhancing their ability to learn and stay informed on various subjects.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Improved Communication:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Learning email basics and using communication tools allows individuals to stay connected with others, fostering improved communication in both personal and professional settings.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Efficient Information Management:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Understanding file management and basic software applications helps individuals organize and manage information efficiently, whether for personal use or work-related tasks.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Increased Productivity:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Proficiency in applications such as word processors and spreadsheets contributes to increased productivity, allowing individuals to create documents, analyze data, and perform routine tasks more efficiently.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>','<p>A Basic Computer Application course offers numerous benefits for individuals who participate, regardless of their background or current skill level. Here are some key advantages:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Enhanced Employability:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Acquiring basic computer skills enhances employability in various industries. Many job roles require at least a fundamental understanding of common software applications and computer usage.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Access to Educational Resources:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Basic computer skills enable individuals to access educational resources online, enhancing their ability to learn and stay informed on various subjects.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Improved Communication:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Learning email basics and using communication tools allows individuals to stay connected with others, fostering improved communication in both personal and professional settings.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Efficient Information Management:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Understanding file management and basic software applications helps individuals organize and manage information efficiently, whether for personal use or work-related tasks.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Increased Productivity:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Proficiency in applications such as word processors and spreadsheets contributes to increased productivity, allowing individuals to create documents, analyze data, and perform routine tasks more efficiently.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>','<p>John Johnson</p>','<p>John Johnson</p>','',13,'2023-12-15 07:16:21','2023-12-15 07:16:21',2),(16,'<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Cambria&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"color:#252525\">The role and scope of the governing body are diverse however among others is to sets top tone of the organization by instituting the good governance and performance standards, ethical culture, effective control and legitimacy with stakeholders to achieve organization goals. &nbsp;Corporate governance plays a crucial role in ensuring the effective management, accountability, and sustainability of organizations.&nbsp; By participating in this Board Induction training, participants&nbsp;&nbsp;will gain the knowledge and skills necessary to make informed decisions, provide effective oversight, and contribute to the strategic direction of the organisation.</span></span></span></span></p>','<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Cambria&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"color:#252525\">The role and scope of the governing body are diverse however among others is to sets top tone of the organization by instituting the good governance and performance standards, ethical culture, effective control and legitimacy with stakeholders to achieve organization goals. &nbsp;Corporate governance plays a crucial role in ensuring the effective management, accountability, and sustainability of organizations.&nbsp; By participating in this Board Induction training, participants&nbsp;&nbsp;will gain the knowledge and skills necessary to make informed decisions, provide effective oversight, and contribute to the strategic direction of the organisation.</span></span></span></span></p>','<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Cambria&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"color:#252525\">Board&nbsp; Members and Management&nbsp; Team.</span></span></span></span></p>','<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Cambria&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"color:#252525\">Board&nbsp; Members and Management&nbsp; Team .</span></span></span></span></p>','<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Cambria&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"color:#252525\">The Board Induction training on Corporate Governance is a comprehensive programme designed specifically for the newly appointed Board. This training aims to equip the Commissioners with the necessary knowledge, skills, and insights to effectively fulfil their roles and responsibilities as board members. Through interactive sessions, case studies, group discussions, and practical exercises, the Commissioners will gain a deep understanding of corporate governance principles, regulatory frameworks, risk management, stakeholder engagement, ethical leadership, and compliance. The training will be conducted by experienced trainer (s) who have a proven track record of delivering high-quality training programmes to similar institutions. The Commissioners will be equipped with the necessary tools to contribute effectively to board discussions, make informed decisions, ensure transparency and accountability, and advance the mission&nbsp; in promoting and regulating science and technology&nbsp;in&nbsp;Tanzania</span></span></span></span></p>','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Cambria&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"color:#252525\">The Board Induction training on Corporate Governance is a comprehensive programme designed specifically for the newly appointed Board. This training aims to equip the Commissioners with the necessary knowledge, skills, and insights to effectively fulfil their roles and responsibilities as board members. Through interactive sessions, case studies, group discussions, and practical exercises, the Commissioners will gain a deep understanding of corporate governance principles, regulatory frameworks, risk management, stakeholder engagement, ethical leadership, and compliance. The training will be conducted by experienced trainer (s) who have a proven track record of delivering high-quality training programmes to similar institutions. The Commissioners will be equipped with the necessary tools to contribute effectively to board discussions, make informed decisions, ensure transparency and accountability, and advance the mission&nbsp; in promoting and regulating science and technology&nbsp;in&nbsp;Tanzania</span></span></span></span></p>','<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Cambria&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"color:#252525\">At the end of training, participants will be able;</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"color:#252525\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Cambria&quot;,serif\">Understanding of Corporate Governance: Develop a comprehensive understanding of corporate governance principles, frameworks, and best practices relevant to&nbsp; enabling members to effectively discharge their responsibilities as board members;</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"color:#252525\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Cambria&quot;,serif\">Role and Responsibilities: Gain clarity on roles and responsibilities of Commissioners, including fiduciary duties, strategic oversight, and accountability to stakeholders;</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"color:#252525\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Cambria&quot;,serif\">Regulatory Compliance: Understand the regulatory landscape governing science and technology in Tanzania and ensure compliance with applicable laws, regulations, and ethical standards;</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"color:#252525\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Cambria&quot;,serif\">Board Effectiveness: Enhance their ability to contribute effectively to board discussions, make informed decisions, and promote transparency, accountability, and ethical conduct within.</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"color:#252525\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Cambria&quot;,serif\">Risk Management: Develop an understanding of risk management principles and strategies, enabling to identify, assess, and mitigate risks associated with&nbsp; operations and programmes; and </span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"color:#252525\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Cambria&quot;,serif\">Ethical Leadership: Promote a culture of ethical leadership, integrity, and professionalism within or ensuring the highest standards of conduct and accountability.</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>','<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Cambria&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"color:#252525\">At the end of training, participants will be able;</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"color:#252525\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Cambria&quot;,serif\">Understanding of Corporate Governance: Develop a comprehensive understanding of corporate governance principles, frameworks, and best practices relevant to&nbsp; enabling members to effectively discharge their responsibilities as board members;</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"color:#252525\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Cambria&quot;,serif\">Role and Responsibilities: Gain clarity on roles and responsibilities of Commissioners, including fiduciary duties, strategic oversight, and accountability to stakeholders;</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"color:#252525\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Cambria&quot;,serif\">Regulatory Compliance: Understand the regulatory landscape governing science and technology in Tanzania and ensure compliance with applicable laws, regulations, and ethical standards;</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"color:#252525\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Cambria&quot;,serif\">Board Effectiveness: Enhance their ability to contribute effectively to board discussions, make informed decisions, and promote transparency, accountability, and ethical conduct within.</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"color:#252525\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Cambria&quot;,serif\">Risk Management: Develop an understanding of risk management principles and strategies, enabling to identify, assess, and mitigate risks associated with&nbsp; operations and programmes; and </span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"color:#252525\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Cambria&quot;,serif\">Ethical Leadership: Promote a culture of ethical leadership, integrity, and professionalism within or ensuring the highest standards of conduct and accountability.</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>','<p>Frank Msewa</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Global learning section&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>0654342428</p>','<p>Frank Msewa</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Global learning section&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>0654342428</p>','',14,'2023-12-15 07:21:55','2023-12-15 07:21:55',2),(17,'<p><strong>TOPICS INCLUDE</strong><br />\r\nOffice management;<br />\r\nAdministrative services management;<br />\r\nManagement functions;<br />\r\nRecords management;<br />\r\nProblem solving and decision making;<br />\r\nInterpersonal and communication skills;<br />\r\nCustomer care ;<br />\r\nPersonal effectiveness;<br />\r\nTeam working skills;<br />\r\nTime management;<br />\r\nManaging stress;<br />\r\nOffice hygiene and etiquette.</p>','<p><strong>COURSE OVERVIEW</strong><br />\r\nOffice assistants typically work with others to make sure that an office functions better. They provide administrative and clerical support for proper functioning of organization offices. They must have many skills in order to perform their duties effectively. These skills are technical, administrative, interpersonal and conceptual. Technical skills are essential for understanding and executing specific duties and clerical routine tasks. Administrative abilities enable one to understand and follow policies and procedures in order to carry out organizational activities in an orderly manner. Interpersonal skills consist of the abilities to understand other people and interact effectively with them. Conceptual skills involve the ability to acquire, analyze, and interpret information in a logical manner. The above skills form the basis of important management and administrative activities such as front office management, customer care, records management, information management, office hygiene etc.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>TOPICS INCLUDE</strong><br />\r\nOffice management;<br />\r\nAdministrative services management;<br />\r\nManagement functions;<br />\r\nRecords management;<br />\r\nProblem solving and decision making;<br />\r\nInterpersonal and communication skills;<br />\r\nCustomer care ;<br />\r\nPersonal effectiveness;<br />\r\nTeam working skills;<br />\r\nTime management;<br />\r\nManaging stress;<br />\r\nOffice hygiene and etiquette.</p>','<p><strong>WHO SHOULD ATTEND?</strong><br />\r\nAll office assistants and people newly appointed to supervisory roles, along with Secretaries and record clerks within the office environment, who want to build on their skills and knowledge</p>','<p><strong>WHO SHOULD ATTEND?</strong><br />\r\nAll office assistants and people newly appointed to supervisory roles, along with Secretaries and record clerks within the office environment, who want to build on their skills and knowledge</p>','<p>Office assistants typically work with others to make sure that an office functions better. They provide administrative and clerical support for proper functioning of organization offices. They must have many skills in order to perform their duties effectively. These skills are technical, administrative, interpersonal and conceptual. Technical skills are essential for understanding and executing specific duties and clerical routine tasks. Administrative abilities enable one to understand and follow policies and procedures in order to carry out organizational activities in an orderly manner. Interpersonal skills consist of the abilities to understand other people and interact effectively with them. Conceptual skills involve the ability to acquire, analyze, and interpret information in a logical manner. The above skills form the basis of important management and administrative activities such as front office management, customer care, records management, information management, office hygiene etc.</p>','<p>Office assistants typically work with others to make sure that an office functions better. They provide administrative and clerical support for proper functioning of organization offices. They must have many skills in order to perform their duties effectively. These skills are technical, administrative, interpersonal and conceptual. Technical skills are essential for understanding and executing specific duties and clerical routine tasks. Administrative abilities enable one to understand and follow policies and procedures in order to carry out organizational activities in an orderly manner. Interpersonal skills consist of the abilities to understand other people and interact effectively with them. Conceptual skills involve the ability to acquire, analyze, and interpret information in a logical manner. The above skills form the basis of important management and administrative activities such as front office management, customer care, records management, information management, office hygiene etc.</p>','<p>At the end of the course, participants will be able to:<br />\r\nEnhance their personal effectiveness and development;<br />\r\nPerform office and administrative functions effectively and efficiently;<br />\r\nImprove ability to independently with less supervision;<br />\r\nDeal with day to day work problems more effectively;<br />\r\nImprove relationships with colleagues and customers;<br />\r\nCommunicate more effectively;<br />\r\nProvide better care to customers;<br />\r\nEnhance hygiene in the work place;<br />\r\nApply proper etiquettes at all times;<br />\r\nHandle stressful situations.</p>','<p><strong>HOW PARTICIPANTS WILL BENEFIT?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>At the end of the course, participants will be able to:<br />\r\nEnhance their personal effectiveness and development;<br />\r\nPerform office and administrative functions effectively and efficiently;<br />\r\nImprove ability to independently with less supervision;<br />\r\nDeal with day to day work problems more effectively;<br />\r\nImprove relationships with colleagues and customers;<br />\r\nCommunicate more effectively;<br />\r\nProvide better care to customers;<br />\r\nEnhance hygiene in the work place;<br />\r\nApply proper etiquettes at all times;<br />\r\nHandle stressful situations.</p>','<p>Short course department<