\":\"Mfumo wa Huduma kwa Watumishi\",\"title_en\":\"ESS\",\"url\":\"https:\\/\\/ess.utumishi.go.tz\"}','2023-12-14 10:47:34','2023-12-14 10:47:34'),(1243,6,'OnlineService','store','41.222.179.24','http://demo81.eganet.go.tz/tpsc/cms/online_services','{\"title_sw\":\"PlanRep\",\"title_en\":\"PlanRep\",\"url\":\"https:\\/\\/planrep.tro.go.tz\\/auth\\/user\\/login\"}','2023-12-14 10:49:02','2023-12-14 10:49:02'),(1244,6,'OnlineService','store','41.222.179.24','http://demo81.eganet.go.tz/tpsc/cms/online_services','{\"title_sw\":\"MUSE\",\"title_en\":\"MUSE\",\"url\":\"https:\\/\\/tanzanite.muse.go.tz\\/\"}','2023-12-14 10:49:28','2023-12-14 10:49:28'),(1245,6,'MenuItem','store','41.222.179.24','http://demo81.eganet.go.tz/tpsc/cms/menu-items','{\"menu_id\":\"11\",\"title_sw\":\"eMrejesho\",\"title_en\":\"eMrejesho\",\"link\":\"0\",\"url_external\":\"https:\\/\\/emrejesho.gov.go.tz\\/\",\"url\":\"https:\\/\\/emrejesho.gov.go.tz\\/\",\"position\":8}','2023-12-14 10:56:55','2023-12-14 10:56:55'),(1246,6,'Campus','store','41.59.251.78','http://demo81.eganet.go.tz/tpsc/cms/campuses','{\"title_sw\":\"Kampasi ya Dar es Salaam\",\"title_en\":\"Dar es Salaam Campus\",\"particulars_sw\":\"<p style=\\\"text-align: justify;\\\">The Tanzania Public Service College Dar es salaam Campus (TPSC) is among of the six campuses for Tanzania Public service College, The campus performs all three core functions of the College which includes Training, Consultancy and Applied Research, but also the Campus provide review Programs for Public Service Examinations, and other Performance Improvement Programs with the aim of building a culture of continuous learning for public servants.<\\/p>\",\"particulars_en\":\"<p>The Tanzania Public Service College Dar es salaam Campus (TPSC) is among of the six campuses for Tanzania Public service College, The campus performs all three core functions of the College which includes Training, Consultancy and Applied Research, but also the Campus provide review Programs for Public Service Examinations, and other Performance Improvement Programs with the aim of building a culture of continuous learning for public servants.<\\/p>\",\"course_offered_sw\":\"<p style=\\\"text-align:justify\\\">Current the Campus runs a range of Programmes from NTA Level 4 to NTA Level 8 which is offered by different Academic Departments such as: Public Sector Financial Management (PSFM), Secretarial Studies (SS), Records and Archives Management (RAM), Public Administration, Leadership and Management (PALM).<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p style=\\\"text-align:justify\\\">Since the establishment of the Campus, the Campus had been offering Programs at Certificate and Diploma levels, yet in meeting Customer needs, the Campus started offering a Bachelor Degree in the areas of Secretarial Studies and records, archives and Information management since September 2017 with a total number of 200 students of which some of them who where qualified for the Loans they are the beneficiary of Loans from the Higher Education Loan Board.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p style=\\\"text-align:justify\\\">Currently the Campus is expecting to run only two Programs; Records management and Secretarial Studies from NTA level 4 to NTA lever 8. At the moment Campus has more than 35 qualified Teaching Staff<\\/p>\",\"course_offered_en\":\"<p style=\\\"text-align: justify;\\\">Current the Campus runs a range of Programmes from NTA Level 4 to NTA Level 8 which is offered by different Academic Departments such as: Public Sector Financial Management (PSFM), Secretarial Studies (SS), Records and Archives Management (RAM), Public Administration, Leadership and Management (PALM).<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p style=\\\"text-align: justify;\\\">Since the establishment of the Campus, the Campus had been offering Programs at Certificate and Diploma levels, yet in meeting Customer needs, the Campus started offering a Bachelor Degree in the areas of Secretarial Studies and records, archives and Information management since September 2017 with a total number of 200 students of which some of them who where qualified for the Loans they are the beneficiary of Loans from the Higher Education Loan Board.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p style=\\\"text-align: justify;\\\">Currently the Campus is expecting to run only two Programs; Records management and Secretarial Studies from NTA level 4 to NTA lever 8. At the moment Campus has more than 35 qualified Teaching Staff<\\/p>\",\"student_services_sw\":\"<p>Student Services Helpdesk<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Gender and Help Desk<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Accommodation Offices&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Useful Contact Details<\\/p>\",\"student_services_en\":\"<p>Student Services Helpdesk<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Gender and Help Desk<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Accommodation Offices&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Useful Contact Details<\\/p>\",\"facilities_sw\":\"<p>Classrooms and Hall<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Typing Laboratories<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Computer Laboratories&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Library<\\/p>\",\"facilities_en\":\"<p>Classrooms and Hall<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Typing Laboratories<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Computer Laboratories&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Library<\\/p>\",\"contacts_sw\":\"<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Mkurugenzi wa Kampasi<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Chuo Cha Utumishi wa Umma Tanzania&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>S.L.P&nbsp; 2574<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Dar es Salaam<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Simu: +255 22 2123547\\/9, 2122243<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Barua pepe:&nbsp; dsm@tpsc.go.tz<\\/p>\",\"contacts_en\":\"<p>&nbsp;Dar es salaam Campus is located at Magogoni Street Opposite Prime Minister Office along Kivukoni Road<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Campus Director<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Tanzania Public Service College<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>P.O Box 2574<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>DSM<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Tel: +255 22 2123547\\/9, 2122243<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>E mail dsm@tpsc.go.tz<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\",\"slug\":\"dar-es-salaam-campus\"}','2023-12-15 06:50:50','2023-12-15 06:50:50'),(1247,6,'Campus','store','41.59.251.78','http://demo81.eganet.go.tz/tpsc/cms/campuses','{\"title_sw\":\"Tanga\",\"title_en\":\"Tanga\",\"particulars_sw\":\"<p>Who are we?<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The Tanzania Public Service College (TPSC) Tanga campus was established in July 2014, being the fourth campus to be established among the six campuses of TPSC. It&rsquo;s establishment was a result of instructions issued by prime minister Hon. Mizengo Pinda on 23th November 2009 during inauguration of Tanzania Public Service College Mtwara Campus.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>At the time of its establishment, it had only one academic programme (i.e. Basic Technician Certificate in Records Management), with 453 students and 9 instructors. At the moment the college has over 5 courses, with more than 50 instructors and over 1,600 students.<\\/p>\",\"particulars_en\":\"<p>Who are we?<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The Tanzania Public Service College (TPSC) Tanga campus was established in July 2014, being the fourth campus to be established among the six campuses of TPSC. It&rsquo;s establishment was a result of instructions issued by prime minister Hon. Mizengo Pinda on 23th November 2009 during inauguration of Tanzania Public Service College Mtwara Campus.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>At the time of its establishment, it had only one academic programme (i.e. Basic Technician Certificate in Records Management), with 453 students and 9 instructors. At the moment the college has over 5 courses, with more than 50 instructors and over 1,600 students.<\\/p>\",\"course_offered_sw\":\"<ol>\\r\\n\\t<li>Records, Archives and Information Management<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Secretarial Studies<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Human Resource Management<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Public Administration<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Procurement and Supply Management<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ol>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\",\"course_offered_en\":\"<ol>\\r\\n\\t<li>Records, Archives and Informatio