store','41.59.251.78','http://demo81.eganet.go.tz/tpsc/cms/short_courses','{\"description_sw\":\"<p>Basic Computer Applications typically cover a range of fundamental concepts and skills related to using computers and common software. Here are the basic topics that may be included in a Basic Computer Applications course:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ol>\\r\\n\\t<li>\\r\\n\\t<p><strong>Introduction to Computers:<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\t<ul>\\r\\n\\t\\t<li>Definition and components of a computer system<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t\\t<li>Understanding hardware and software<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\t<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>\\r\\n\\t<p><strong>Operating Systems:<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\t<ul>\\r\\n\\t\\t<li>Basics of operating systems (e.g., Windows, macOS, Linux)<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t\\t<li>File management and navigation<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\t<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>\\r\\n\\t<p><strong>Word Processing:<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\t<ul>\\r\\n\\t\\t<li>Using word processing software (e.g., Microsoft Word, Google Docs)<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t\\t<li>Creating, editing, and formatting documents<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t\\t<li>Working with tables and images<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\t<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>\\r\\n\\t<p><strong>Spreadsheets:<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\t<ul>\\r\\n\\t\\t<li>Introduction to spreadsheet software (e.g., Microsoft Excel, Google Sheets)<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t\\t<li>Creating and formatting spreadsheets<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t\\t<li>Formulas and functions for calculations<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\t<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>\\r\\n\\t<p><strong>Presentations:<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\t<ul>\\r\\n\\t\\t<li>Creating and delivering presentations<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t\\t<li>Using presentation software (e.g., Microsoft PowerPoint, Google Slides)<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t\\t<li>Incorporating multimedia elements<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\t<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>\\r\\n\\t<p><strong>Internet Basics:<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\t<ul>\\r\\n\\t\\t<li>Web browsers and navigation<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t\\t<li>Understanding URLs and websites<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t\\t<li>Internet safety and security<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\t<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>\\r\\n\\t<p><strong>Email and Communication:<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\t<ul>\\r\\n\\t\\t<li>Using email for communication<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t\\t<li>Attachments and email etiquette<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t\\t<li>Online communication tools (e.g., messaging apps)<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\t<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>\\r\\n\\t<p><strong>Basic Computer Security:<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\t<ul>\\r\\n\\t\\t<li>Password management<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t\\t<li>Antivirus software and malware protection<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t\\t<li>Safe internet browsing practices<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\t<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>\\r\\n\\t<p><strong>File Management and Backup:<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\t<ul>\\r\\n\\t\\t<li>Organizing files and folders<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t\\t<li>Creating backups and restoring data<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\t<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>\\r\\n\\t<p><strong>Introduction to Software Applications:<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\t<ul>\\r\\n\\t\\t<li>Overview of common software applications (e.g., Adobe Acrobat, image editing tools)<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t\\t<li>Installing and uninstalling software<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\t<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>\\r\\n\\t<p><strong>Computer Hardware Awareness:<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\t<ul>\\r\\n\\t\\t<li>Understanding computer hardware components (CPU, RAM, storage)<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t\\t<li>Basic troubleshooting and maintenance<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\t<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>\\r\\n\\t<p><strong>Cloud Computing:<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\t<ul>\\r\\n\\t\\t<li>Basics of cloud storage and services<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t\\t<li>Uploading and sharing files using cloud platforms<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\t<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>\\r\\n\\t<p><strong>Collaborative Tools:<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\t<ul>\\r\\n\\t\\t<li>Introduction to collaborative platforms (e.g., Google Workspace, Microsoft Teams)<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t\\t<li>Online document collaboration<\\/l