libarick ana Shahada ya Kwanza ya Menenimenti ya Mifumo na Shahada ya Uzamili ya Mifumo.<\\/p>\",\"content_en\":\"<p style=\\\"text-align:justify\\\">Mr. Elibarick Mushi assumed the role of Director of Academic Support Services (Acting) in November 2023. Prior to his current position, he served in various key roles at Tanzania Public Service College, including Head of Quality Assurance (1.5 years), Head of ICT (1.5 years), Manager of Programmes (4 years), Campus Head of Admission and Examination Unit (3 years), and Campus ICT Coordinator (1 year). Before joining TPSC, he served for four years as an Assistant Lecturer and Tutorial Assistant at Kampala International University.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p style=\\\"text-align:justify\\\">With 13 years of dedicated experience in higher education, coupled with passion about utilizing technology to enhance business operations, Elibarick has played a pivotal role in shaping the next generation of ICT professionals and inspiring students from diverse fields to leverage ICT for improved performance in their respective professions. His training expertise spans computer programming, web applications development, Information Systems, database design, and office applications.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p style=\\\"text-align:justify\\\">In addition to his teaching roles, Elibarick&#39;s exposure to managerial and administrative duties has honed his skills in Administration, Curriculum Development and Implementation, Policy Formulation, Quality Assurance in Colleges, and Academic Committees&rsquo; Management.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p style=\\\"text-align:justify\\\">Elibarick holds a Bachelor&#39;s degree in Management Information Systems and a Master&#39;s degree in Information Systems.<\\/p>\",\"photo_url\":\"882fc34c01729e46b8ff8307fd754e2e.png\",\"email\":\"elibarick.mushi@tpsc.go.tz\",\"phone\":\"0753860432\",\"created_at\":\"2023-12-14T11:49:50.000000Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2023-12-16T15:05:54.000000Z\",\"slug\":\"director\"}','2023-12-16 12:10:14