ife to Students in Vocational &nbsp;Education and Training Institutions; The case of Mtwara &nbsp;region and &nbsp;Exploring &nbsp;the Influence of Parenting &nbsp;Style on Adolescents&rsquo; Sexual Behavior (Prostitution) in Chris Mwangi&rsquo;s The Operator. Further underscoring her unwavering commitment to advancing the fields of education and personal development. She frequently involved in personal academic studies online and attending short course training particularly on data collection and analysis.<\\/p>\",\"content_en\":\"<p style=\\\"text-align:justify\\\">Ms. Juslina M.Tuzza is An Assistant Lecturer and Campus Director at the Tanzania Public Service College (TPSC) - Mtwara Campus. &nbsp;She is a highly accomplished professional in the fields of education (Language). She holds a Master&rsquo;s Degree of Arts with Education from the University of Dar es Salaam, Tanzania. She also holds a Bachelor of Arts with Education from the University of St. John Dodoma-Tanzania and a Diploma in Education from the Marangu Teachers&rsquo; College- Kilimanjaro, Tanzania.<br \\/>\\r\\nIn March 2021, she joined Tanzania Public Service Collage as Assistant lecturer, where latter promoted to the position of Manager of Program at Campus level, a position she held until February 2022, when she was appointed as Campus Director at Mtwara campus working from February 2022 to date<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p style=\\\"text-align:justify\\\"><br \\/>\\r\\nIn her role as the Campus Director at Tanzania Public Service College- Mtwara, Ms. Tuzza is responsible for the implementation of all policies and initiatives aimed at ensuring the efficiency and accountability of the campus staff and students in implementing their responsibilities to make sure specific and general goals of the organization are well attained. She is highly dedicated and her successful career path and an upward mobility that is matched and can only be explained by factors of individual motivation and personal discipline as well as sense of self-awareness fueled by her individual strong and persistence philosophy of life.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p style=\\\"text-align:justify\\\"><br \\/>\\r\\nMs. Juslina M Tuzza has a remarkable academic background, combined with her experiences and skills have made significant contributions to the development and advancement of the Tanzania Public College at Mtwara Campus and Nation at large. Besides, She has successfully prepared papers for publication; The Perception of Job seekers on the Adoption and Use of E-Recruitment in Tanzania:A case study of Ajira Portal, Challenges of &nbsp;&lsquo; Gheto&rsquo; life to Students in Vocational &nbsp;Education and Training Institutions; The case of Mtwara &nbsp;region and &nbsp;Exploring &nbsp;the Influence of Parenting &nbsp;Style on Adolescents&rsquo; Sexual Behavior (Prostitution) in Chris Mwangi&rsquo;s The Operator. Further underscoring her unwavering commitment to advancing the fields of education and personal development. She frequently involved in personal academic studies online and attending short course training particularly on data collection and analysis.<\\/p>\",\"photo_url\":\"c169c419cbfa83870ad64df47a602160.jpeg\",\"email\":\"juslina.tuzza@tpsc.go.tz\",\"phone\":\"Phone: +255 232 333300\",\"created_at\":\"2023-12-14T11:55:16.000000Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2024-01-11T06:54:06.000000Z\",\"slug\":\"campus-manager-mtwara-campus\"}','2024-01-11 03:55:25','2024-01-11 03:55:25'),(1500,6,'Campus','update','41.222.181.211','http://demo81.eganet.go.tz/tpsc/cms/campuses/8','{\"id\":8,\"particulars_sw\":\"<p>Chuo cha Utumishi wa Umma Kampasi ya Mtwara kilizinduliwa na Waziri Mkuu Mh. Mizengo Peter Pinda Tarehe 23 Novemba, 2009.Katika uzinduzi huo kampasi ilikuwa na jumla ya wanafunzi 261 na watumishi 7.Kwa sasa Kampasi ina wanafunzi zaidi ya 2000 na watumishi 57.Mwanzoni Kampasi hii ilikusudiwa kuhudumia Kanda na Mikoa mitatu (Mtwara, Lindi na Ruvuma) kwa sababu za mazingira yao ya kijografia na historia kimeshindwa kuvutia watu kusafiri kuja Dar es salaam na Tabora kwa ajili ya mafunzo zaidi. Kwa hiyo Kampasi ya Mtwara pamekuwa mahali pa kuanzia kwa watu wa Mikoa ya Kusini kujiunga na mafunzo ya elimu ya juu.Kwa sasa Kampasi ya Mtwara inatoa mafunzo kwa Mikoa ya Kusini pamoja na Mikoa yote ya Tanzania.Ina wanafunzi takribani kutoka kila Mkoa wa Tanzania.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><strong>Tuko wapi?<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Kampasi ya Mtwara (TPSC) ipo sehemu yakusini ya Tanzania katika Mkoa wa Mtwara, eneo la Shangani Mashariki, karibu na Nyumba za Shirika la Nyumba Tanzania Shangani na Hospitali ya Tawi la Ndanda.Kama ukiwa Kituo Kikuu chaMabasi cha Mkoa au mahali kwengine kokote katika Mji wa Mtwara, Chukua Usafiri wa Bodaboda mwambie derive akupeleke &ldquo;Chuo cha Utumishi Mtwara&rdquo;<\\/p>\",\"course_offered_sw\":\"<p>Utunzaji wa kumbukumbu.......\\/.<\\/p>\",\"student_services_sw\":\"<p>1. Medical services&nbsp;<br \\/>\\r\\nThe Campus has collaboration with nearby Health centers which provides clinical and health services. This nearby Health Centre&rsquo;s provides for referral cases to Ligula Regional Hospital and Southern Zone Referral Hospital where facilities for serious medication and surgical attention exist. Nevertheless, the campus encourages staff and students to join the National Health Insurance Fund (NHIF) which guarantees the medical treatment at the nearby health centers and regional hospital. Upon admission, all students are required to pay medical capitation fees and receive medical services based on these fees.&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><br \\/>\\r\\n2. Accommodation services&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Students are accommodated by nearby private hostels which are approved by the campus management. The list of private hostels and the contacts are normally attached with the admission letters.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>3. Academic Support<br \\/>\\r\\nThe campus utilizes opportunity to develop skills, knowledge and insights through well researched, designed competence-based programmes, resourced by highly qualified and registered CBET training providers. The campus has taken all measures to make sure that the information provided is current and accurate, in terms of staffing, curricula, course contents and teaching facilities.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>5. Tanzania Public Service Student&rsquo;s Organization (TAPSSO)<br \\/>\\r\\nFormal student activities are administered by the Tanzania Public Service Student&rsquo;s Organization (TAPSSO). TAPSSO is concerned with students&rsquo; academic, social and recreational activities. Every campus student is automatically a member of TAPSSO. Most of the students&rsquo; activities are organized by the student organization. The student organization addresses itself on aspects of representing students&rsquo; interest on various campus decision making bodies. TAPSSO under the leadership of its President is a formal active voice of students, within and outside the campus. Besides, under TAPSSO there are professional academic associations (affiliated to TAPSSO) such as religious, Environment protection, PCCB club, Ethics club as well as Campus choir.<\\/p>\",\"facilities_sw\":\"<p>1. Classrooms<br \\/>\\r\\nThe campus has total of nine (9) classrooms, two (2) computer laboratories, one (1) typing room, and one (1) registry model.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>2. Campus Library<br \\/>\\r\\nThe campus Library contains up-to-date book collections in the fields of Management, Administration, Secretarial studies, Records and Archive management, Law, ICT, and Statistics. The library currently comprises of about 2000 book volumes that cater for all the courses conducted at the campus. The library can accommodate about 80 readers at a time. The books stock is classified and arranged according to the Dewey Decimal Classification Scheme 22nd edition and catalogued according to the Anglo American Cataloguing Rules (AACR) 2nd edition Revised in 2002. The library produces Library Rules and Guide as may be required within an academic year. The Guide and rules are for distribution to fresh students during the orientation week and they are required to read and abide by them. Moreover, there is growing collection of e-library that accompanies some new books. This database is important because it provide more information in various subject areas.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>3.Games and Sports<br \\/>\\r\\nThe campus use nearby facilities for out-doors games such as football, basketball, netball and volleyball. The campus also has sports equipment such as balls for all mentioned games, jerseys, whistles, ball pumps, stop watches, corner flags, and nets of different games to mention few. Currently there are two appointed games tutors who organize and co-ordinate all games and sports activities for both staff and students in and out of the campus. Therefore, all students are expected and encouraged to have sports outfit.<\\/p>\",\"contacts_sw\":\"<p><em>Mkurugenzi wa Kampasi<\\/em><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Chuo cha Utumishi wa Umma Tanzania<\\/em><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>S.L.P 1051<\\/em><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><strong><em>Mtwara<\\/em><\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Simu:<\\/em><em>&nbsp;<\\/em>: +255 232 333300<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Nukushi<\\/em><em>&nbsp;<\\/em>+255 232 333300<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Barua Pepe:<\\/em><em>&nbsp;<\\/em>mtwara@tpsc.go.tz<\\/p>\",\"particulars_en\":\"<p>TPSC Mtwara campus is a branch of Tanzania Public Service College which was officially inaugurated by the Prime Minister Honourable Mizengo Peter Pinda on the 23rd November 2009. At its inauguration, it had a total of 261 students with 7 staffs. Currently, it has over 2,000 students with 57 staffs. Initially the campus was aimed at catering the three southern zonal regions (Mtwara, Lindi and Ruvuma) as their geographical and historical background failed to attract people travelling to Dar es Salaam and Tabora to pursue their further studies. Hence Mtwara Campus has been a stepping stone for southern regions people to join to higher studies.<br \\/>\\r\\nIn the mean time, TPSC Mtwara is not only serving the southern regions but all regions in Tanzania. It has students comming from almost every regions in Tanzania.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><strong>Where are We?<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>TPSC Mtwara campus is located at the southern part of Tanzania, in Mtwara region, at the Shangani East area, near National housing houses Shangani and Ndanda branch hospital. If you are at the main regional bus stand (or any where around Mtwara town), pick a Bodaboda and ask the driver to bring you to &quot;Chuo cha utumishi Mtwara&quot;<\\/p>\",\"course_offered_en\":\"<p>Records and archaive management........<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\",\"student_services_en\":\"<p>1. Medical services&nbsp;<br \\/>\\r\\nThe Campus has collaboration with nearby Health centers which provides clinical and health services. This nearby Health Centre&rsquo;s provides for referral cases to Ligula Regional Hospital and Southern Zone Referral Hospital where facilities for serious medication and surgical attention exist. Nevertheless, the campus encourages staff and students to join the National Health Insurance Fund (NHIF) which guarantees the medical treatment at the nearby health centers and regional hospital. Upon admission, all students are required to pay medical capitation fees and receive medical services based on these fees.&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><br \\/>\\r\\n2. Accommodation services&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Students are accommodated by nearby private hostels which are approved by the campus management. The list of private hostels and the contacts are normally attached with the admission letters.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>3. Academic Support<br \\/>\\r\\nThe campus utilizes opportunity to develop skills, knowledge and insights through well researched, designed competence-based programmes, resourced by highly qualified and registered CBET training providers. The campus has taken all measures to make sure that the information provided is current and accurate, in terms of staffing, curricula, course contents and teaching facilities.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>5. Tanzania Public Service Student&rsquo;s Organization (TAPSSO)<br \\/>\\r\\nFormal student activities are administered by the Tanzania Public Service Student&rsquo;s Organization (TAPSSO). TAPSSO is concerned with students&rsquo; academic, social and recreational activities. Every campus student is automatically a member of TAPSSO. Most of the students&rsquo; activities are organized by the student organization. The student organization addresses itself on aspects of representing students&rsquo; interest on various campus decision making bodies. TAPSSO under the leadership of its President is a formal active voice of students, within and outside the campus. Besides, under TAPSSO there are professional academic associations (affiliated to TAPSSO) such as religious, Environment protection, PCCB club, Ethics club as well as Campus choir.<\\/p>\",\"facilities_en\":\"<p>1. Classrooms<br \\/>\\r\\nThe campus has total of nine (9) classrooms, two (2) computer laboratories, one (1) typing room, and one (1) registry model.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>2. Campus Library<br \\/>\\r\\nThe campus Library contains up-to-date book collections in the fields of Management, Administration, Secretarial studies, Records and Archive management, Law, ICT, and Statistics. The library currently comprises of about 2000 book volumes that cater for all the courses conducted at the campus. The library can accommodate about 80 readers at a time. The books stock is classified and arranged according to the Dewey Decimal Classification Scheme 22nd edition and catalogued according to the Anglo American Cataloguing Rules (AACR) 2nd edition Revised in 2002. The library produces Library Rules and Guide as may be required within an academic year. The Guide and rules are for distribution to fresh students during the orientation week and they are required to read and abide by them. Moreover, there is growing collection of e-library that accompanies some new books. This database is important because it provide more information in various subject areas.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>3.Games and Sports<br \\/>\\r\\nThe campus use nearby facilities for out-doors games such as football, basketball, netball and volleyball. The campus also has sports equipment such as balls for all mentioned games, jerseys, whistles, ball pumps, stop watches, corner flags, and nets of different games to mention few. Currently there are two appointed games tutors who organize and co-ordinate all games and sports activities for both staff and students in and out of the campus. Therefore, all students are expected and encouraged to have sports outfit.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>,&nbsp;<\\/p>\",\"contacts_en\":\"<p>Campus Director<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>TPSC Mtwara Campus<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>P.O.Box 1051<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Mtwara<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Phone: +255 232 333300<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Fax: +255 232 333300<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Email: mtwara@tpsc.go.tz<\\/p>\",\"slug\":\"mtwara-campus\",\"title_sw\":\"Kampasi ya Mtwara\",\"title_en\":\"Mtwara Campus\",\"created_at\":\"2023-12-15T09:56:56.000000Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2023-12-15T09:56:56.000000Z\"}','2024-01-11 04:08:11','2024-01-11 04:08:11'),(1501,6,'Campus','update','41.222.181.211','http://demo81.eganet.go.tz/tpsc/cms/campuses/10','{\"id\":10,\"particulars_sw\":\"<p style=\\\"text-align:justify\\\">Tanzania Public Service College &ndash; Singida Campus is one of the six (6) Campuses of the Tanzania Public Service College (TPSC). The Campus was established in July 2011, being the fourth campus to be established among the six campuses of TPSC. Its establishment was a result of instructions issued by Prime Minister Hon. Mizengo Pinda on 23rd November 2009 during inauguration of Tanzania Public Service College Mtwara Campus. Singida Campus is located along airport road in Mandewa Ward at Singida Municipality &ndash;Singida Region.&nbsp;<\\/p>\",\"course_offered_sw\":\"<p style=\\\"text-align:justify\\\">The Campus offers a wide range of programmes from Certificate to Diploma levels. The courses offered include Basic Technician Certificate in Secretarial Studies (BTCSS) &ndash; NTA 4; Basic Technician Certificate in Records Management (BTCRM) - NTA 4; Basic Technician Certificate in Human Resource Management (BTCHRM) &ndash; NTA 4; Basic Technician Certificate in Public Administration (BTCPA) &ndash; NTA 4; Ordinary Diploma in Secretarial Studies (ODSS) &ndash; NTA 5 &amp; 6; Ordinary Diploma in Records Management (ODRM) (NTA 5 &amp; 6); Ordinary Diploma in Public Administration (ODPA) &ndash; NTA 5 &amp; 6 and Ordinary Diploma in Human Resource Management (ODHRM)&ndash;NTA 5 &amp; 6. Likewise, the Campus offers short courses and consultant services to different stakeholders in the public and private sector. It is also the centre for coordinating and conducting Public Service Examinations (PSE) to public servants. Singida Campus follows Competence Based Education Training (CBET) curricula and positions itself to practice all its endeavors at the highest level of standards<\\/p>\",\"student_services_sw\":\"<p style=\\\"text-align:justify\\\">To enable students acquire necessary skills for professionalism and career development in different areas of specialization the campus has ensured-:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p style=\\\"text-align:justify\\\">a)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Reliable catering and banking services to facilitate &nbsp;availability of food and banking services at affordable cost<br \\/>\\r\\nb)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Good climatic condition surrounded by greenish environment that makes learning and studying environment conducive.&nbsp;<br \\/>\\r\\nc)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;The accommodation services: The campus offers a range of quality accommodation services both on-campus and off-campus. Off campus accommodation services are handled in collaboration with private owners of hostels but under the management and control of Campus management. The services are charged at the rate of TZS. 150,000-200,000\\/= per &nbsp;semester&nbsp;<br \\/>\\r\\nd)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Government and private owned health facilities including Singida Regional Referral Hospital, Singida Municipal Hospital, Tumaini Health Centre and MICO Health Centre that provide high quality, responsive and sustainable health services are all located nearby the Campus.<br \\/>\\r\\ne)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Religious facilities including churches for Christian students and Mosque for Muslims students are available for enhancing students&rsquo; spiritual life. Apart from that, campus provides building for worshipping services for all Christians and Muslims students who need extra religious services.<br \\/>\\r\\nf)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Sports and games facilities that aim to promote overall health and mental ability of the students and teachers. Sports facilities available include football pitches, netball, and volleyball among others.&nbsp;<br \\/>\\r\\ng)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Health Insurance services which are provided in collaboration with National Health Insurance Funds (NHIF) are ensured to students for ease and quality acquisition of health services at the affordable cost.<br \\/>\\r\\nh)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Counseling services that aims to offer services targeting health related concerns; academic (teaching and learning) concerns; psycho-social concerns; economic and financial concerns and other personal concerns. Likewise, the section commensurate with provision of high-quality services that nurture students to engage in academic and social development effectively.<\\/p>\",\"facilities_sw\":\"<p style=\\\"text-align:justify\\\">The campus provides academic services in well ventilated and modern classrooms, laboratories (both typing and computer laboratories) with a well-equipped library that contain modern and current books, internet and learning facilities. Teaching and learning activities are facilitated by well and highly qualified, motivated, committed and talented facilitators who are eager to serve the customers with high level of loyalty and integrity.&nbsp;<\\/p>\",\"contacts_sw\":null,\"particulars_en\":\"<p style=\\\"text-align:justify\\\">Tanzania Public Service College &ndash; Singida Campus is one of the six (6) Campuses of the Tanzania Public Service College (TPSC). The Campus was established in July 2011, being the fourth campus to be established among the six campuses of TPSC. Its establishment was a result of instructions issued by Prime Minister Hon. Mizengo Pinda on 23rd November 2009 during inauguration of Tanzania Public Service College Mtwara Campus. Singida Campus is located along airport road in Mandewa Ward at Singida Municipality &ndash;Singida Region.<\\/p>\",\"course_offered_en\":\"<p style=\\\"text-align:justify\\\">The Campus offers a wide range of programmes from Certificate to Diploma levels. The courses offered include Basic Technician Certificate in Secretarial Studies (BTCSS) &ndash; NTA 4; Basic Technician Certificate in Records Management (BTCRM) - NTA 4; Basic Technician Certificate in Human Resource Management (BTCHRM) &ndash; NTA 4; Basic Technician Certificate in Public Administration (BTCPA) &ndash; NTA 4; Ordinary Diploma in Secretarial Studies (ODSS) &ndash; NTA 5 &amp; 6; Ordinary Diploma in Records Management (ODRM) (NTA 5 &amp; 6); Ordinary Diploma in Public Administration (ODPA) &ndash; NTA 5 &amp; 6 and Ordinary Diploma in Human Resource Management (ODHRM)&ndash;NTA 5 &amp; 6. Likewise, the Campus offers short courses and consultant services to different stakeholders in the public and private sector. It is also the centre for coordinating and conducting Public Service Examinations (PSE) to public servants. Singida Campus follows Competence Based Education Training (CBET) curricula and positions itself to practice all its endeavors at the highest level of standards<\\/p>\",\"student_services_en\":\"<p style=\\\"text-align:justify\\\">To enable students acquire necessary skills for professionalism and career development in different areas of specialization the campus has ensured-:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p style=\\\"text-align:justify\\\">a)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Reliable catering and banking services to facilitate &nbsp;availability of food and banking services at affordable cost<br \\/>\\r\\nb)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Good climatic condition surrounded by greenish environment that makes learning and studying environment conducive.&nbsp;<br \\/>\\r\\nc)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;The accommodation services: The campus offers a range of quality accommodation services both on-campus and off-campus. Off campus accommodation services are handled in collaboration with private owners of hostels but under the management and control of Campus management. The services are charged at the rate of TZS. 150,000-200,000\\/= per &nbsp;semester&nbsp;<br \\/>\\r\\nd)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Government and private owned health facilities including Singida Regional Referral Hospital, Singida Municipal Hospital, Tumaini Health Centre and MICO Health Centre that provide high quality, responsive and sustainable health services are all located nearby the Campus.<br \\/>\\r\\ne)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Religious facilities including churches for Christian students and Mosque for Muslims students are available for enhancing students&rsquo; spiritual life. Apart from that, campus provides building for worshipping services for all Christians and Muslims students who need extra religious services.<br \\/>\\r\\nf)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Sports and games facilities that aim to promote overall health and mental ability of the students and teachers. Sports facilities available include football pitches, netball, and volleyball among others.&nbsp;<br \\/>\\r\\ng)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Health Insurance services which are provided in collaboration with National Health Insurance Funds (NHIF) are ensured to students for ease and quality acquisition of health services at the affordable cost.<br \\/>\\r\\nh)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Counseling services that aims to offer services targeting health related concerns; academic (teaching and learning) concerns; psycho-social concerns; economic and financial concerns and other personal concerns. Likewise, the section commensurate with provision of high-quality services that nurture students to engage in academic and social development effectively.<\\/p>\",\"facilities_en\":\"<p style=\\\"text-align:justify\\\">The campus provides academic services in well ventilated and modern classrooms, laboratories (both typing and computer laboratories) with a well-equipped library that contain modern and current books, internet and learning facilities. Teaching and learning activities are facilitated by well and highly qualified, motivated, committed and talented facilitators who are eager to serve the customers with high level of loyalty and integrity.&nbsp;<\\/p>\",\"contacts_en\":null,\"slug\":\"singida-campus\",\"title_sw\":\"KAMPASI YA SINGIDA\",\"title_en\":\"SINGIDA CAMPUA\",\"created_at\":\"2024-01-09T21:55:29.000000Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2024-01-09T21:55:29.000000Z\"}','2024-01-11 04:10:08','2024-01-11 04:10:08'),(1502,6,'Campus','update','41.222.181.211','http://demo81.eganet.go.tz/tpsc/cms/campuses/9','{\"id\":9,\"particulars_sw\":\"<p style=\\\"text-align:justify\\\">The Global Learning Centre (GLC) is a Directorate of Tanzania Public Service College (TPSC). It is a capacity building centre with wide-range capacity building interventions that include; Leadership and Managerial Skills development, Board Governance and Leadership, Fraud investigation, Fundamentals of Regulation in Utility Services and other regulatory areas (water, oil, electricity and Gas, weather), Change Management, Transformation Leadership, Financial management, Project management, Team Building and Coaching, Human Resource management, Counselling and Guidance, and Enterprise Risk Management. GLC is also a member of the Global Development<br \\/>\\r\\nLearning Network (GDLN) which is a partnership of over 120 recognised global institutions (ffiliates) in over 80 countries that collaborates in the design of customised learning solutions for individuals and organisations working in development.<\\/p>\",\"course_offered_sw\":\"<p>.<\\/p>\",\"student_services_sw\":\"<p>.<\\/p>\",\"facilities_sw\":\"<p>-.<\\/p>\",\"contacts_sw\":\"<p>.<\\/p>\",\"particulars_en\":\"<p style=\\\"text-align:justify\\\">The Global Learning Centre (GLC) is a Directorate of Tanzania Public Service College (TPSC). It is a capacity building centre with wide-range capacity building interventions that include; Leadership and Managerial Skills development, Board Governance and Leadership, Fraud investigation, Fundamentals of Regulation in Utility Services and other regulatory areas (water, oil, electricity and Gas, weather), Change Management, Transformation Leadership, Financial management, Project management, Team Building and Coaching, Human Resource management, Counselling and Guidance, and Enterprise Risk Management. GLC is also a member of the Global Development<br \\/>\\r\\nLearning Network (GDLN) which is a partnership of over 120 recognised global institutions (ffiliates) in over 80 countries that collaborates in the design of customised learning solutions for individuals and organisations working in development.<\\/p>\",\"course_offered_en\":\"<p>.<\\/p>\",\"student_services_en\":\"<p>.<\\/p>\",\"facilities_en\":\"<p>.<\\/p>\",\"contacts_en\":\"<p>.<\\/p>\",\"slug\":\"global-learning-section\",\"title_sw\":\"KITUO CHA MAFUNZO KWA NJIA YA MTANDAO\",\"title_en\":\"GLOBAL LEARNING SECTION\",\"created_at\":\"2023-12-15T10:00:46.000000Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2023-12-15T10:00:46.000000Z\"}','2024-01-11 04:11:09','2024-01-11 04:11:09'),(1503,6,'Campus','update','41.222.181.211','http://demo81.eganet.go.tz/tpsc/cms/campuses/8','{\"id\":8,\"particulars_sw\":\"<p>Chuo cha Utumishi wa Umma Kampasi ya Mtwara kilizinduliwa na Waziri Mkuu Mh. Mizengo Peter Pinda Tarehe 23 Novemba, 2009.Katika uzinduzi huo kampasi ilikuwa na jumla ya wanafunzi 261 na watumishi 7.Kwa sasa Kampasi ina wanafunzi zaidi ya 2000 na watumishi 57.Mwanzoni Kampasi hii ilikusudiwa kuhudumia Kanda na Mikoa mitatu (Mtwara, Lindi na Ruvuma) kwa sababu za mazingira yao ya kijografia na historia kimeshindwa kuvutia watu kusafiri kuja Dar es salaam na Tabora kwa ajili ya mafunzo zaidi. Kwa hiyo Kampasi ya Mtwara pamekuwa mahali pa kuanzia kwa watu wa Mikoa ya Kusini kujiunga na mafunzo ya elimu ya juu.Kwa sasa Kampasi ya Mtwara inatoa mafunzo kwa Mikoa ya Kusini pamoja na Mikoa yote ya Tanzania.Ina wanafunzi takribani kutoka kila Mkoa wa Tanzania.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><strong>Tuko wapi?<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Kampasi ya Mtwara (TPSC) ipo sehemu yakusini ya Tanzania katika Mkoa wa Mtwara, eneo la Shangani Mashariki, karibu na Nyumba za Shirika la Nyumba Tanzania Shangani na Hospitali ya Tawi la Ndanda.Kama ukiwa Kituo Kikuu chaMabasi cha Mkoa au mahali kwengine kokote katika Mji wa Mtwara, Chukua Usafiri wa Bodaboda mwambie derive akupeleke &ldquo;Chuo cha Utumishi Mtwara&rdquo;<\\/p>\",\"course_offered_sw\":\"<p>Utunzaji wa kumbukumbu.......\\/.<\\/p>\",\"student_services_sw\":\"<p>1. Medical services&nbsp;<br \\/>\\r\\nThe Campus has collaboration with nearby Health centers which provides clinical and health services. This nearby Health Centre&rsquo;s provides for referral cases to Ligula Regional Hospital and Southern Zone Referral Hospital where facilities for serious medication and surgical attention exist. Nevertheless, the campus encourages staff and students to join the National Health Insurance Fund (NHIF) which guarantees the medical treatment at the nearby health centers and regional hospital. Upon admission, all students are required to pay medical capitation fees and receive medical services based on these fees.&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><br \\/>\\r\\n2. Accommodation services&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Students are accommodated by nearby private hostels which are approved by the campus management. The list of private hostels and the contacts are normally attached with the admission letters.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>3. Academic Support<br \\/>\\r\\nThe campus utilizes opportunity to develop skills, knowledge and insights through well researched, designed competence-based programmes, resourced by highly qualified and registered CBET training providers. The campus has taken all measures to make sure that the information provided is current and accurate, in terms of staffing, curricula, course contents and teaching facilities.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>5. Tanzania Public Service Student&rsquo;s Organization (TAPSSO)<br \\/>\\r\\nFormal student activities are administered by the Tanzania Public Service Student&rsquo;s Organization (TAPSSO). TAPSSO is concerned with students&rsquo; academic, social and recreational activities. Every campus student is automatically a member of TAPSSO. Most of the students&rsquo; activities are organized by the student organization. The student organization addresses itself on aspects of representing students&rsquo; interest on various campus decision making bodies. TAPSSO under the leadership of its President is a formal active voice of students, within and outside the campus. Besides, under TAPSSO there are professional academic associations (affiliated to TAPSSO) such as religious, Environment protection, PCCB club, Ethics club as well as Campus choir.<\\/p>\",\"facilities_sw\":\"<p>1. Classrooms<br \\/>\\r\\nThe campus has total of nine (9) classrooms, two (2) computer laboratories, one (1) typing room, and one (1) registry model.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>2. Campus Library<br \\/>\\r\\nThe campus Library contains up-to-date book collections in the fields of Management, Administration, Secretarial studies, Records and Archive management, Law, ICT, and Statistics. The library currently comprises of about 2000 book volumes that cater for all the courses conducted at the campus. The library can accommodate about 80 readers at a time. The books stock is classified and arranged according to the Dewey Decimal Classification Scheme 22nd edition and catalogued according to the Anglo American Cataloguing Rules (AACR) 2nd edition Revised in 2002. The library produces Library Rules and Guide as may be required within an academic year. The Guide and rules are for distribution to fresh students during the orientation week and they are required to read and abide by them. Moreover, there is growing collection of e-library that accompanies some new books. This database is important because it provide more information in various subject areas.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>3.Games and Sports<br \\/>\\r\\nThe campus use nearby facilities for out-doors games such as football, basketball, netball and volleyball. The campus also has sports equipment such as balls for all mentioned games, jerseys, whistles, ball pumps, stop watches, corner flags, and nets of different games to mention few. Currently there are two appointed games tutors who organize and co-ordinate all games and sports activities for both staff and students in and out of the campus. Therefore, all students are expected and encouraged to have sports outfit.<\\/p>\",\"contacts_sw\":\"<p><em>Mkurugenzi wa Kampasi<\\/em><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Chuo cha Utumishi wa Umma Tanzania<\\/em><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>S.L.P 1051<\\/em><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><strong><em>Mtwara<\\/em><\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Simu:<\\/em><em>&nbsp;<\\/em>: +255 232 333300<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Nukushi<\\/em><em>&nbsp;<\\/em>+255 232 333300<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Barua Pepe:<\\/em><em>&nbsp;<\\/em>mtwara@tpsc.go.tz<\\/p>\",\"particulars_en\":\"<p>TPSC Mtwara campus is a branch of Tanzania Public Service College which was officially inaugurated by the Prime Minister Honourable Mizengo Peter Pinda on the 23rd November 2009. At its inauguration, it had a total of 261 students with 7 staffs. Currently, it has over 2,000 students with 57 staffs. Initially the campus was aimed at catering the three southern zonal regions (Mtwara, Lindi and Ruvuma) as their geographical and historical background failed to attract people travelling to Dar es Salaam and Tabora to pursue their further studies. Hence Mtwara Campus has been a stepping stone for southern regions people to join to higher studies.<br \\/>\\r\\nIn the mean time, TPSC Mtwara is not only serving the southern regions but all regions in Tanzania. It has students comming from almost every regions in Tanzania.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><strong>Where are We?<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>TPSC Mtwara campus is located at the southern part of Tanzania, in Mtwara region, at the Shangani East area, near National housing houses Shangani and Ndanda branch hospital. If you are at the main regional bus stand (or any where around Mtwara town), pick a Bodaboda and ask the driver to bring you to &quot;Chuo cha utumishi Mtwara&quot;<\\/p>\",\"course_offered_en\":\"<p>Records and archaive management........<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\",\"student_services_en\":\"<p>1. Medical services&nbsp;<br \\/>\\r\\nThe Campus has collaboration with nearby Health centers which provides clinical and health services. This nearby Health Centre&rsquo;s provides for referral cases to Ligula Regional Hospital and Southern Zone Referral Hospital where facilities for serious medication and surgical attention exist. Nevertheless, the campus encourages staff and students to join the National Health Insurance Fund (NHIF) which guarantees the medical treatment at the nearby health centers and regional hospital. Upon admission, all students are required to pay medical capitation fees and receive medical services based on these fees.&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><br \\/>\\r\\n2. Accommodation services&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Students are accommodated by nearby private hostels which are approved by the campus management. The list of private hostels and the contacts are normally attached with the admission letters.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>3. Academic Support<br \\/>\\r\\nThe campus utilizes opportunity to develop skills, knowledge and insights through well researched, designed competence-based programmes, resourced by highly qualified and registered CBET training providers. The campus has taken all measures to make sure that the information provided is current and accurate, in terms of staffing, curricula, course contents and teaching facilities.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>5. Tanzania Public Service Student&rsquo;s Organization (TAPSSO)<br \\/>\\r\\nFormal student activities are administered by the Tanzania Public Service Student&rsquo;s Organization (TAPSSO). TAPSSO is concerned with students&rsquo; academic, social and recreational activities. Every campus student is automatically a member of TAPSSO. Most of the students&rsquo; activities are organized by the student organization. The student organization addresses itself on aspects of representing students&rsquo; interest on various campus decision making bodies. TAPSSO under the leadership of its President is a formal active voice of students, within and outside the campus. Besides, under TAPSSO there are professional academic associations (affiliated to TAPSSO) such as religious, Environment protection, PCCB club, Ethics club as well as Campus choir.<\\/p>\",\"facilities_en\":\"<p>1. Classrooms<br \\/>\\r\\nThe campus has total of nine (9) classrooms, two (2) computer laboratories, one (1) typing room, and one (1) registry model.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>2. Campus Library<br \\/>\\r\\nThe campus Library contains up-to-date book collections in the fields of Management, Administration, Secretarial studies, Records and Archive management, Law, ICT, and Statistics. The library currently comprises of about 2000 book volumes that cater for all the courses conducted at the campus. The library can accommodate about 80 readers at a time. The books stock is classified and arranged according to the Dewey Decimal Classification Scheme 22nd edition and catalogued according to the Anglo American Cataloguing Rules (AACR) 2nd edition Revised in 2002. The library produces Library Rules and Guide as may be required within an academic year. The Guide and rules are for distribution to fresh students during the orientation week and they are required to read and abide by them. Moreover, there is growing collection of e-library that accompanies some new books. This database is important because it provide more information in various subject areas.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>3.Games and Sports<br \\/>\\r\\nThe campus use nearby facilities for out-doors games such as football, basketball, netball and volleyball. The campus also has sports equipment such as balls for all mentioned games, jerseys, whistles, ball pumps, stop watches, corner flags, and nets of different games to mention few. Currently there are two appointed games tutors who organize and co-ordinate all games and sports activities for both staff and students in and out of the campus. Therefore, all students are expected and encouraged to have sports outfit.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>,&nbsp;<\\/p>\",\"contacts_en\":\"<p>Campus Director<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>TPSC Mtwara Campus<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>P.O.Box 1051<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Mtwara<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Phone: +255 232 333300<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Fax: +255 232 333300<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Email: mtwara@tpsc.go.tz<\\/p>\",\"slug\":\"mtwara-campus\",\"title_sw\":\"Kampasi ya Mtwara  KAMPASI YA MTWARA\",\"title_en\":\"MTWARA CAMPUS\",\"created_at\":\"2024-01-11T10:08:11.000000Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2024-01-11T07:08:11.000000Z\"}','2024-01-11 04:11:36','2024-01-11 04:11:36'),(1504,6,'Campus','update','41.222.181.211','http://demo81.eganet.go.tz/tpsc/cms/campuses/8','{\"id\":8,\"particulars_sw\":\"<p>Chuo cha Utumishi wa Umma Kampasi ya Mtwara kilizinduliwa na Waziri Mkuu Mh. Mizengo Peter Pinda Tarehe 23 Novemba, 2009.Katika uzinduzi huo kampasi ilikuwa na jumla ya wanafunzi 261 na watumishi 7.Kwa sasa Kampasi ina wanafunzi zaidi ya 2000 na watumishi 57.Mwanzoni Kampasi hii ilikusudiwa kuhudumia Kanda na Mikoa mitatu (Mtwara, Lindi na Ruvuma) kwa sababu za mazingira yao ya kijografia na historia kimeshindwa kuvutia watu kusafiri kuja Dar es salaam na Tabora kwa ajili ya mafunzo zaidi. Kwa hiyo Kampasi ya Mtwara pamekuwa mahali pa kuanzia kwa watu wa Mikoa ya Kusini kujiunga na mafunzo ya elimu ya juu.Kwa sasa Kampasi ya Mtwara inatoa mafunzo kwa Mikoa ya Kusini pamoja na Mikoa yote ya Tanzania.Ina wanafunzi takribani kutoka kila Mkoa wa Tanzania.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><strong>Tuko wapi?<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Kampasi ya Mtwara (TPSC) ipo sehemu yakusini ya Tanzania katika Mkoa wa Mtwara, eneo la Shangani Mashariki, karibu na Nyumba za Shirika la Nyumba Tanzania Shangani na Hospitali ya Tawi la Ndanda.Kama ukiwa Kituo Kikuu chaMabasi cha Mkoa au mahali kwengine kokote katika Mji wa Mtwara, Chukua Usafiri wa Bodaboda mwambie derive akupeleke &ldquo;Chuo cha Utumishi Mtwara&rdquo;<\\/p>\",\"course_offered_sw\":\"<p>Utunzaji wa kumbukumbu.......\\/.<\\/p>\",\"student_services_sw\":\"<p>1. Medical services&nbsp;<br \\/>\\r\\nThe Campus has collaboration with nearby Health centers which provides clinical and health services. This nearby Health Centre&rsquo;s provides for referral cases to Ligula Regional Hospital and Southern Zone Referral Hospital where facilities for serious medication and surgical attention exist. Nevertheless, the campus encourages staff and students to join the National Health Insurance Fund (NHIF) which guarantees the medical treatment at the nearby health centers and regional hospital. Upon admission, all students are required to pay medical capitation fees and receive medical services based on these fees.&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><br \\/>\\r\\n2. Accommodation services&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Students are accommodated by nearby private hostels which are approved by the campus management. The list of private hostels and the contacts are normally attached with the admission letters.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>3. Academic Support<br \\/>\\r\\nThe campus utilizes opportunity to develop skills, knowledge and insights through well researched, designed competence-based programmes, resourced by highly qualified and registered CBET training providers. The campus has taken all measures to make sure that the information provided is current and accurate, in terms of staffing, curricula, course contents and teaching facilities.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>5. Tanzania Public Service Student&rsquo;s Organization (TAPSSO)<br \\/>\\r\\nFormal student activities are administered by the Tanzania Public Service Student&rsquo;s Organization (TAPSSO). TAPSSO is concerned with students&rsquo; academic, social and recreational activities. Every campus student is automatically a member of TAPSSO. Most of the students&rsquo; activities are organized by the student organization. The student organization addresses itself on aspects of representing students&rsquo; interest on various campus decision making bodies. TAPSSO under the leadership of its President is a formal active voice of students, within and outside the campus. Besides, under TAPSSO there are professional academic associations (affiliated to TAPSSO) such as religious, Environment protection, PCCB club, Ethics club as well as Campus choir.<\\/p>\",\"facilities_sw\":\"<p>1. Classrooms<br \\/>\\r\\nThe campus has total of nine (9) classrooms, two (2) computer laboratories, one (1) typing room, and one (1) registry model.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>2. Campus Library<br \\/>\\r\\nThe campus Library contains up-to-date book collections in the fields of Management, Administration, Secretarial studies, Records and Archive management, Law, ICT, and Statistics. The library currently comprises of about 2000 book volumes that cater for all the courses conducted at the campus. The library can accommodate about 80 readers at a time. The books stock is classified and arranged according to the Dewey Decimal Classification Scheme 22nd edition and catalogued according to the Anglo American Cataloguing Rules (AACR) 2nd edition Revised in 2002. The library produces Library Rules and Guide as may be required within an academic year. The Guide and rules are for distribution to fresh students during the orientation week and they are required to read and abide by them. Moreover, there is growing collection of e-library that accompanies some new books. This database is important because it provide more information in various subject areas.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>3.Games and Sports<br \\/>\\r\\nThe campus use nearby facilities for out-doors games such as football, basketball, netball and volleyball. The campus also has sports equipment such as balls for all mentioned games, jerseys, whistles, ball pumps, stop watches, corner flags, and nets of different games to mention few. Currently there are two appointed games tutors who organize and co-ordinate all games and sports activities for both staff and students in and out of the campus. Therefore, all students are expected and encouraged to have sports outfit.<\\/p>\",\"contacts_sw\":\"<p><em>Mkurugenzi wa Kampasi<\\/em><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Chuo cha Utumishi wa Umma Tanzania<\\/em><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>S.L.P 1051<\\/em><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><strong><em>Mtwara<\\/em><\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Simu:<\\/em><em>&nbsp;<\\/em>: +255 232 333300<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Nukushi<\\/em><em>&nbsp;<\\/em>+255 232 333300<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Barua Pepe:<\\/em><em>&nbsp;<\\/em>mtwara@tpsc.go.tz<\\/p>\",\"particulars_en\":\"<p>TPSC Mtwara campus is a branch of Tanzania Public Service College which was officially inaugurated by the Prime Minister Honourable Mizengo Peter Pinda on the 23rd November 2009. At its inauguration, it had a total of 261 students with 7 staffs. Currently, it has over 2,000 students with 57 staffs. Initially the campus was aimed at catering the three southern zonal regions (Mtwara, Lindi and Ruvuma) as their geographical and historical background failed to attract people travelling to Dar es Salaam and Tabora to pursue their further studies. Hence Mtwara Campus has been a stepping stone for southern regions people to join to higher studies.<br \\/>\\r\\nIn the mean time, TPSC Mtwara is not only serving the southern regions but all regions in Tanzania. It has students comming from almost every regions in Tanzania.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><strong>Where are We?<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>TPSC Mtwara campus is located at the southern part of Tanzania, in Mtwara region, at the Shangani East area, near National housing houses Shangani and Ndanda branch hospital. If you are at the main regional bus stand (or any where around Mtwara town), pick a Bodaboda and ask the driver to bring you to &quot;Chuo cha utumishi Mtwara&quot;<\\/p>\",\"course_offered_en\":\"<p>Records and archaive management........<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\",\"student_services_en\":\"<p>1. Medical services&nbsp;<br \\/>\\r\\nThe Campus has collaboration with nearby Health centers which provides clinical and health services. This nearby Health Centre&rsquo;s provides for referral cases to Ligula Regional Hospital and Southern Zone Referral Hospital where facilities for serious medication and surgical attention exist. Nevertheless, the campus encourages staff and students to join the National Health Insurance Fund (NHIF) which guarantees the medical treatment at the nearby health centers and regional hospital. Upon admission, all students are required to pay medical capitation fees and receive medical services based on these fees.&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><br \\/>\\r\\n2. Accommodation services&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Students are accommodated by nearby private hostels which are approved by the campus management. The list of private hostels and the contacts are normally attached with the admission letters.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>3. Academic Support<br \\/>\\r\\nThe campus utilizes opportunity to develop skills, knowledge and insights through well researched, designed competence-based programmes, resourced by highly qualified and registered CBET training providers. The campus has taken all measures to make sure that the information provided is current and accurate, in terms of staffing, curricula, course contents and teaching facilities.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>5. Tanzania Public Service Student&rsquo;s Organization (TAPSSO)<br \\/>\\r\\nFormal student activities are administered by the Tanzania Public Service Student&rsquo;s Organization (TAPSSO). TAPSSO is concerned with students&rsquo; academic, social and recreational activities. Every campus student is automatically a member of TAPSSO. Most of the students&rsquo; activities are organized by the student organization. The student organization addresses itself on aspects of representing students&rsquo; interest on various campus decision making bodies. TAPSSO under the leadership of its President is a formal active voice of students, within and outside the campus. Besides, under TAPSSO there are professional academic associations (affiliated to TAPSSO) such as religious, Environment protection, PCCB club, Ethics club as well as Campus choir.<\\/p>\",\"facilities_en\":\"<p>1. Classrooms<br \\/>\\r\\nThe campus has total of nine (9) classrooms, two (2) computer laboratories, one (1) typing room, and one (1) registry model.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>2. Campus Library<br \\/>\\r\\nThe campus Library contains up-to-date book collections in the fields of Management, Administration, Secretarial studies, Records and Archive management, Law, ICT, and Statistics. The library currently comprises of about 2000 book volumes that cater for all the courses conducted at the campus. The library can accommodate about 80 readers at a time. The books stock is classified and arranged according to the Dewey Decimal Classification Scheme 22nd edition and catalogued according to the Anglo American Cataloguing Rules (AACR) 2nd edition Revised in 2002. The library produces Library Rules and Guide as may be required within an academic year. The Guide and rules are for distribution to fresh students during the orientation week and they are required to read and abide by them. Moreover, there is growing collection of e-library that accompanies some new books. This database is important because it provide more information in various subject areas.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>3.Games and Sports<br \\/>\\r\\nThe campus use nearby facilities for out-doors games such as football, basketball, netball and volleyball. The campus also has sports equipment such as balls for all mentioned games, jerseys, whistles, ball pumps, stop watches, corner flags, and nets of different games to mention few. Currently there are two appointed games tutors who organize and co-ordinate all games and sports activities for both staff and students in and out of the campus. Therefore, all students are expected and encouraged to have sports outfit.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>,&nbsp;<\\/p>\",\"contacts_en\":\"<p>Campus Director<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>TPSC Mtwara Campus<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>P.O.Box 1051<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Mtwara<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Phone: +255 232 333300<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Fax: +255 232 333300<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Email: mtwara@tpsc.go.tz<\\/p>\",\"slug\":\"mtwara-campus\",\"title_sw\":\"KAMPASI YA MTWARA\",\"title_en\":\"MTWARA CAMPUS\",\"created_at\":\"2024-01-11T10:11:36.000000Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2024-01-11T07:11:36.000000Z\"}','2024-01-11 04:11:54','2024-01-11 04:11:54'),(1505,6,'Campus','update','41.222.181.211','http://demo81.eganet.go.tz/tpsc/cms/campuses/7','{\"id\":7,\"particulars_sw\":\"<p><strong>Kampasi ya Tabora kwa Ufupi<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p style=\\\"text-align:justify\\\">Chuo cha Utumishi wa Umma Tanzania (TPSC) Kampasi ya Tabora kilichokuwa kikijulikana kwa jina la Chuo cha Uhazili Tabora ni Kampasi ya pili ya zamani baada ya Kampasi ya Dar es Salaam kilichokuwa kikijulikana kama Chuo cha Mafunzo ya Utumishi wa Serikali. Chuo cha Uhazili Tabora kilianzishwa ili kujaza pengo la upungufu wa watumishi wa Ofisini na hasa Wahazili baada ya kupata Uhuru Tanzania. Ujenzi wa Chuo ulianza Septemba 1970 na kukamilika na kuanza kufanya kazi Oktoba, 1973. Chuo hiki kimekuwa na mabweni manne ya wanafunzi 600, wanaume 300 na wanawake 300 na maeneo ya michezo na burudani.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p style=\\\"text-align:justify\\\">Mwaka 2000 Chuo cha Uhazili Tabora na Chuo cha Mafunzo cha Utumishi wa Serikali viliunda Chuo cha Utumishi wa Umma Tanzania kwa Sheria ya Wakala za Serikali Na. ya 2000.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p style=\\\"text-align:justify\\\">Wakati wa kuanzishwa kwake ilikuwa na mihula miwili ya wiki 21 kwa mwaka, hasa kutilia mkazo Mafunzo ya awali na Mafunzo tarajali ya Uhazili na wakufunzi 29 tu. Hivi sasa Kampasi hii ina zaidi ya kozi 5, na wakufunzi wa kudumu 23 na wa muda 21 na Zaidi ya wanafunzi 2563 wanachukua program za Cheti na Diploma.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><strong><em><u>Tuko wapi?<\\/u><\\/em><\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Chuo cha Utumishi wa Umma Tanzania Kampasi ya Tabora kipo Mtaa wa Itetemya, Kata ya Kanyenye Manispaa ya Tabora mkabala na Makao makuu ya&nbsp; Polisi mkoa wa Tabora.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\",\"course_offered_sw\":\"<p>The following programmes are offered at Tabora Campus;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ol>\\r\\n\\t<li>Uhazili (NTAL Level 4 to NTA Level 6)<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Utunzaji Kumbukumbu, Nyaraka, na Taarifa (NTAL Level 4 to NTA Level 6)<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Menejimenti ya Rasilimali watu (NTAL Level 4 to NTA Level 6)<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ol>\",\"student_services_sw\":\"<p><strong>Huduma za Malazi<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>-----<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><strong>Huduma za Afya<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>-----<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><strong>Dawati la Jinsia<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>-----<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><strong>Ushauri Nasaha<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>-----<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><strong>Serikali ya Wanafunzi<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>-----<\\/p>\",\"facilities_sw\":\"<p><strong>Madarasa<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>----<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><strong>Maabara za Upigaji Chapa<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>----<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><strong>Maabara za Kompyuta<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>----<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><strong>Maktaba<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>-----<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\",\"contacts_sw\":\"<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Mkurugenzi wa Kampasi<\\/em><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Chuo cha Utumishi wa Umma Tanzania<\\/em><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>S.L.P 329<\\/em><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em><strong>Tabora<\\/strong><\\/em><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Simu: +255 26 260 5387<\\/em><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Nukusi: +255 26 260 45 37<\\/em><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Barua Pepe: <a>tabora@tpsc.go.tz<\\/a><\\/em><\\/p>\",\"particulars_en\":\"<p><strong>Tabora Campus overview<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p style=\\\"text-align:justify\\\">Chuo cha Utumishi wa Umma Tanzania (TPSC) Kampasi ya Tabora kilichokuwa kikijulikana kwa jina la Chuo cha Uhazili Tabora ni Kampasi ya pili ya zamani baada ya Kampasi ya Dar es Salaam kilichokuwa kikijulikana kama Chuo cha Mafunzo ya Utumishi wa Serikali. Chuo cha Uhazili Tabora kilianzishwa ili kujaza pengo la upungufu wa watumishi wa Ofisini na hasa Wahazili baada ya kupata Uhuru Tanzania. Ujenzi wa Chuo ulianza Septemba 1970 na kukamilika na kuanza kufanya kazi Oktoba, 1973. Chuo hiki kimekuwa na mabweni manne ya wanafunzi 600, wanaume 300 na wanawake 300 na maeneo ya michezo na burudani.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p style=\\\"text-align:justify\\\">Mwaka 2000 Chuo cha Uhazili Tabora na Chuo cha Mafunzo cha Utumishi wa Serikali viliunda Chuo cha Utumishi wa Umma Tanzania kwa Sheria ya Wakala za Serikali Na. ya 2000.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p style=\\\"text-align:justify\\\">Wakati wa kuanzishwa kwake ilikuwa na mihula miwili ya wiki 21 kwa mwaka, hasa kutilia mkazo Mafunzo ya awali na Mafunzo tarajali ya Uhazili na wakufunzi 29 tu. Hivi sasa Kampasi hii ina zaidi ya kozi 5, na wakufunzi wa kudumu 23 na wa muda 21 na Zaidi ya wanafunzi 2563 wanachukua program za Cheti na Diploma.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><strong><em><u>Tuko wapi?<\\/u><\\/em><\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Chuo cha Utumishi wa Umma Tanzania Kampasi ya Tabora kipo Mtaa wa Itetemya, Kata ya Kanyenye Manispaa ya Tabora mkabala na Makao makuu ya&nbsp; Polisi mkoa wa Tabora.<\\/p>\",\"course_offered_en\":\"<p>The following programmes are offered at Tabora Campus;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ol>\\r\\n\\t<li>Secretarial Studies (NTAL Level 4 to NTA Level 6)<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Records, Archives and Information Management (NTAL Level 4 to NTA Level 6)<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Human Resource Management (NTAL Level 4 to NTA Level 6)<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ol>\",\"student_services_en\":\"<p><strong>Accomodation<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>-----<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><strong>Health Service<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>-----<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><strong>Gender Issues<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>-----<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><strong>Guidance and Support<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>-----<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><strong>Students&#39; Government<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>-----<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><strong>Cafeteria Services<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>-----<\\/p>\",\"facilities_en\":\"<p><strong>Madarasa<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>----<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><strong>Maabara za Upigaji Chapa<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>----<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><strong>Maabara za Kompyuta<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>----<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><strong>Maktaba<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>-----<\\/p>\",\"contacts_en\":\"<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Campus Director<\\/em><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Tanzania Public Service College<\\/em><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>P.O BOX 329,<\\/em><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em><strong>Tabora<\\/strong><\\/em><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Phone: +255 26 260 5387<\\/em><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Fax: +255 26 260 45 37<\\/em><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Email: <a>tabora@tpsc.go.tz<\\/a><\\/em><\\/p>\",\"slug\":\"kampasi-ya-tabora\",\"title_sw\":\"KAMPASI YA TABORA\",\"title_en\":\"TABORA CAMPUS\",\"created_at\":\"2023-12-15T13:03:35.000000Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2023-12-15T10:03:35.000000Z\"}','2024-01-11 04:12:33','2024-01-11 04:12:33'),(1506,6,'Campus','update','41.222.181.211','http://demo81.eganet.go.tz/tpsc/cms/campuses/6','{\"id\":6,\"particulars_sw\":\"<p><strong><em>Who are We?<\\/em><\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Tanzania Public Service College (TPSC) Mbeya Campus was established in July 2014, being the sixth campus to be established among the six campuses of TPSC. Its establishment was a result of instructions issued by Prime Minister Hon. Mizengo Pinda on 23<sup>rd<\\/sup>&nbsp;November 2009 during the inauguration of Tanzania Public Service College Mtwara Campus.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>At the time of its establishment, it had only one academic programme (i.e Basic Technician Certificate in Records Management) with 453 Students and 5 instructors<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><strong><em>Where are we?<\\/em><\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>TPSC Mbeya Campus is located at Sokomatola area nearby CCM regional offices.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><strong>Google Map<\\/strong><\\/p>\",\"course_offered_sw\":\"<p>&nbsp;Courses Offered are as shown here under.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<table cellspacing=\\\"0\\\" style=\\\"border-collapse:collapse; width:531px\\\">\\r\\n\\t<tbody>\\r\\n\\t\\t<tr>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<td style=\\\"border-bottom:none; border-left:none; border-right:none; border-top:none; height:19px; vertical-align:bottom; white-space:nowrap; width:531px\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<ul>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<li><span style=\\\"font-size:15px\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Calibri\\\">Ordinary Diploma in Human Resource Management (ODHRM)&ndash;NTA 5 &amp; 6<\\/span><\\/span><\\/li>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<\\/td>\\r\\n\\t\\t<\\/tr>\\r\\n\\t\\t<tr>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\